WEBVTT

1
00:00:16.280 --> 00:00:18.560
(light music playing)

2
00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:21.400
(birds chirping)

3
00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:40.880
(indistinct chatter)

4
00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:46.720
That sounds nice.

5
00:00:46.840 --> 00:00:48.200
Let's go and try
some diamonds on. yeah?

6
00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:49.800
Okay. yeah that sounds good.

7
00:00:52.120 --> 00:00:53.560
(Helen) Oh. are you all right. pet?

8
00:00:53.640 --> 00:00:55.040
Yeah. Don't make a fuss.
I'm... I'm fine!

9
00:00:55.160 --> 00:00:56.760
Okay. come on.
let's go and get some coffee.

10
00:00:58.040 --> 00:01:00.760
(gasps) Oh. look. come on.

11
00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:02.560
-What? No. No. No. No.
-Yes. Come on.

12
00:01:02.760 --> 00:01:03.920
Oh. We have to try one on?

13
00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:06.120
-Yes. Come on.
-(laughs) What're you doing?

14
00:01:06.200 --> 00:01:09.319
Not that one. Oh look.
this red one. come on.

15
00:01:09.520 --> 00:01:10.920
-Okay.
-Try it on.

16
00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:13.959
-(laughs)
-Hey. that looks good. No?

17
00:01:14.160 --> 00:01:15.160
-No. I like it.
-(Helen) Yeah?

18
00:01:15.319 --> 00:01:16.680
-Yeah.
-(laughs)

19
00:01:16.959 --> 00:01:18.240
(door lock clicks)

20
00:01:20.200 --> 00:01:22.480
-(Helen gasps)
-(chuckles)

21
00:01:28.400 --> 00:01:30.840
Yeah. Let's get it. Hmm?

22
00:01:31.040 --> 00:01:33.480
-Really?
-No. no. it's my treat.

23
00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:36.840
-(gasps) Thank you.
-Oh.

24
00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:46.480
Thank you so much for this.
It's really cheered me up.

25
00:01:46.640 --> 00:01:47.880
It's all right. love.

26
00:01:48.440 --> 00:01:49.800
(chuckles softly)

27
00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:56.200
(brakes squealing)

28
00:01:58.400 --> 00:01:59.600
(car engine stops)

29
00:02:01.520 --> 00:02:02.720
I'll be fine.

30
00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:05.800
All right. pet.

31
00:02:13.960 --> 00:02:17.520
(tense music playing)

32
00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:31.680
(indistinct announcement
over PA)

33
00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:39.880
(breathing heavily)

34
00:02:42.639 --> 00:02:46.520
(panting heavily)

35
00:02:47.520 --> 00:02:48.880
(Lee) Gabi. wait.

36
00:02:50.200 --> 00:02:53.000
-Come on. we need to talk.
-I said leave me alone!

37
00:02:53.240 --> 00:02:56.800
(indistinct chatter)

38
00:02:57.800 --> 00:02:58.960
(music fades)

39
00:02:59.120 --> 00:03:01.880
-(train horn blaring)
-(birds chirping in distance)

40
00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:09.360
(pensive music playing)

41
00:03:47.800 --> 00:03:50.040
(train horn blaring)

42
00:04:06.200 --> 00:04:07.200
Hello?

43
00:04:07.360 --> 00:04:08.560
(signalman) Hello. you are through

44
00:04:08.640 --> 00:04:10.160
to Fensham Point
Crossing Safety Line.

45
00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:12.680
-Is the track clear?
-(signalman) Yes.

46
00:04:14.120 --> 00:04:15.960
So. you think
you're gonna beat us. do you?

47
00:04:16.080 --> 00:04:17.080
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

48
00:04:17.160 --> 00:04:18.600
-You're not going to beat me.
-Yeah. I am.

49
00:04:18.680 --> 00:04:20.040
You know how your dad was
polo champion

50
00:04:20.120 --> 00:04:22.080
-by the time he was your age...
-(Niall) No you wasn't...

51
00:04:22.160 --> 00:04:23.200
I was. I was.

52
00:04:23.279 --> 00:04:24.680
(train horn blaring)

53
00:04:29.320 --> 00:04:30.680
(music fades)

54
00:04:30.839 --> 00:04:32.880
(theme music playing)

55
00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:47.800
{\an8}(theme music concludes)

56
00:04:52.680 --> 00:04:55.680
{\an8}(upbeat music plays)

57
00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:10.279
(groans)

58
00:05:37.520 --> 00:05:38.520
{\an8}(music concludes)

59
00:05:38.600 --> 00:05:40.520
{\an8}-(car horn honking)
-(Steph) Morning. ma'am.

60
00:05:40.600 --> 00:05:42.560
{\an8}Is this as close as I can get?

61
00:05:42.760 --> 00:05:44.279
(Steph) Yeah. sorry.
It's a bit backed up.

62
00:05:44.600 --> 00:05:47.160
Er. it's a maintenance road
used for the level crossing.

63
00:05:47.320 --> 00:05:48.720
Only way vehicles can access it.

64
00:05:51.600 --> 00:05:54.520
(birds chirping)

65
00:05:56.120 --> 00:05:57.120
(groans)

66
00:05:57.880 --> 00:05:58.880
Okay. ma'am?

67
00:06:00.560 --> 00:06:02.600
Oh. DI Ashworth is keen.

68
00:06:04.400 --> 00:06:08.279
So. this level crossing.
it's just for pedestrians. is it?

69
00:06:08.400 --> 00:06:09.720
-(Steph) Yes. ma'am.
-(Vera) Hmm.

70
00:06:12.920 --> 00:06:14.320
(indistinct chatter)

71
00:06:15.320 --> 00:06:16.839
(Joe) No stone unturned.

72
00:06:17.320 --> 00:06:18.640
What's he doing?

73
00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:20.320
(Steph) Ma'am?

74
00:06:20.440 --> 00:06:22.160
(Joe) I want a search
along the length of the track.

75
00:06:22.240 --> 00:06:24.080
and I want a team knocking
on every house

76
00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:25.640
and farm in the area.

77
00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:27.240
Come back to me as soon as you can.

78
00:06:27.360 --> 00:06:28.880
-(officer) Sir.
-(Vera) What's this?

79
00:06:29.279 --> 00:06:32.279
Need I bother turning up?
Have you solved it already?

80
00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:33.720
Thank you. everyone.

81
00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:35.839
-Just getting things started.
-Where's the deceased?

82
00:06:36.040 --> 00:06:38.200
Over there.
She was found by ramblers.

83
00:06:40.800 --> 00:06:42.240
We've stopped the trains
while we work.

84
00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:43.600
Oh. well. that's nice to know.

85
00:06:43.680 --> 00:06:46.760
We're not going to be flattened
by a high-speed express.

86
00:06:50.640 --> 00:06:51.960
Right. thanks.

87
00:06:57.760 --> 00:06:59.160
Vera. you made it.

88
00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:01.839
Well. it's a bit of a walk
from back there.

89
00:07:02.200 --> 00:07:03.240
DI Ashworth.

90
00:07:06.040 --> 00:07:08.320
So... (groans)
...what can you tell us?

91
00:07:08.600 --> 00:07:10.600
We have a female. Early twenties.

92
00:07:10.840 --> 00:07:13.200
Looks a little undernourished.
but otherwise healthy.

93
00:07:14.280 --> 00:07:16.880
Well. undernourished
doesn't exactly scream

94
00:07:17.200 --> 00:07:18.800
regular rambler. does it?

95
00:07:19.120 --> 00:07:20.520
Nor do her clothes.

96
00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.280
-Or those nails...
-Not your style.

97
00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:25.800
Overnight rains made a mess
of the ground.

98
00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:28.720
but I think she fell here.
Not moved post-mortem.

99
00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:31.440
-Anything to give us ID?
-She'd nothing on her.

100
00:07:31.560 --> 00:07:33.560
No purse. no bank cards. no mobile.

101
00:07:33.680 --> 00:07:35.200
Hence getting a search started.

102
00:07:35.760 --> 00:07:37.000
Could have been a theft gone wrong.

103
00:07:37.520 --> 00:07:40.760
(Vera) It's hardly a likely spot
for a mugging. is it?

104
00:07:42.080 --> 00:07:43.400
How long's she been here?

105
00:07:43.640 --> 00:07:45.800
(Paula) Late afternoon yesterday.
early evening maybe.

106
00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:48.000
And cause of death?

107
00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:51.240
Tricky. Possibly asphyxiation.

108
00:07:51.480 --> 00:07:54.280
There are petechial haemorrhages
on the inside of the eyelids.

109
00:07:54.640 --> 00:07:55.840
but no strangle marks.

110
00:07:56.280 --> 00:07:57.400
And rain notwithstanding.

111
00:07:57.480 --> 00:07:59.160
the ground doesn't look scuffed
from a struggle.

112
00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:01.520
And on her cheek.
is that a slap mark?

113
00:08:01.800 --> 00:08:05.800
Er. likely. yes. Plus. see here?
Bruising.

114
00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:08.560
Looks like she was grabbed
by someone hard.

115
00:08:08.880 --> 00:08:11.000
Well. that's a struggle in my book.

116
00:08:11.160 --> 00:08:13.440
(Paula) Also. on her back.

117
00:08:14.320 --> 00:08:16.160
Looks like a full injury to me.

118
00:08:16.560 --> 00:08:18.640
All the bruises.
ante-mortem. of course.

119
00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:21.720
Well. strangled or not.
she was in a fight.

120
00:08:22.520 --> 00:08:25.320
-Any indication of sexual assault?
-No. thankfully.

121
00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:27.480
But I can tell you more
once I get her to the lab.

122
00:08:28.040 --> 00:08:31.040
But at this point. while I can't
definitively say it's murder...

123
00:08:31.200 --> 00:08:33.720
-No. It's not looking good.
-No.

124
00:08:34.080 --> 00:08:37.720
Well. finding her out here
all on her own told me that. love.

125
00:08:38.880 --> 00:08:40.200
Well. thanks. Paula.

126
00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:47.720
(dramatic music playing)

127
00:09:01.160 --> 00:09:04.559
Now. I think we should assume
she's not a regular hiker.

128
00:09:04.679 --> 00:09:06.880
So. what's she doing here? Hmm?

129
00:09:07.520 --> 00:09:09.800
Is she local? How'd she get here?

130
00:09:10.640 --> 00:09:13.600
Dropped off by car.
Walked from a train station.

131
00:09:13.760 --> 00:09:16.360
Yeah. was she with anyone?
Meeting someone?

132
00:09:16.440 --> 00:09:17.440
(Mark) Ma'am.

133
00:09:17.520 --> 00:09:19.120
Have we started that search
along the tracks yet

134
00:09:19.200 --> 00:09:20.520
-and the door knocks?
-(Mark) Er. yes.

135
00:09:20.600 --> 00:09:23.840
and I'll check for any CCTV
spots that might help.

136
00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:25.840
Oh. well.
I won't hold my breath on that.

137
00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:29.360
Er. the rail company are hassling
for when they can reopen the line.

138
00:09:29.440 --> 00:09:32.440
Oh. well. that's an easy one. Mark.
It'll be when I'm done.

139
00:09:32.880 --> 00:09:34.400
-Ma'am.
-Now. where's Kenny?

140
00:09:34.520 --> 00:09:36.640
Is he the only one of us
having a lie-in?

141
00:09:36.760 --> 00:09:37.760
Along there.

142
00:09:37.840 --> 00:09:39.600
He's talking to the rambler
who found the dead body.

143
00:09:39.800 --> 00:09:40.800
Oh. right.

144
00:09:40.960 --> 00:09:43.320
I'd like to talk to this rambler
myself.

145
00:09:43.720 --> 00:09:46.080
Joe. you stay here.
supervise the search.

146
00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:51.880
(Darren) I've been getting Niall
into hiking.

147
00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:55.679
Planned a dawn walk. you know.
catch the sunrise.

148
00:09:56.040 --> 00:09:57.559
Ah. see something beautiful.

149
00:09:58.400 --> 00:10:00.800
(Vera) Yeah. and where
have you come from. love?

150
00:10:01.120 --> 00:10:03.679
-We live in Fensham.
-A couple of miles north. then.

151
00:10:03.960 --> 00:10:05.000
I know.

152
00:10:05.360 --> 00:10:07.480
Walk south. aim to go east
over the tracks

153
00:10:07.559 --> 00:10:08.559
and then loop back up.

154
00:10:09.040 --> 00:10:10.600
But then you saw...

155
00:10:11.360 --> 00:10:13.120
Aye.
I thought she as plastic at first.

156
00:10:13.600 --> 00:10:15.200
Like a mannequin or something.
you know.

157
00:10:16.280 --> 00:10:18.480
And then I realised
and I pulled him back.

158
00:10:19.080 --> 00:10:20.400
So you didn't recognise her?

159
00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:21.520
(Darren) Me? No. no.

160
00:10:21.679 --> 00:10:23.400
Now. are you sure. love?
Did you get a good look?

161
00:10:24.120 --> 00:10:25.800
You're not asking us
to look again. are you?

162
00:10:28.080 --> 00:10:29.400
Nah. you're all right. pet.

163
00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:32.440
Now. is there anything else
you can tell us

164
00:10:32.520 --> 00:10:33.880
that might help. love?

165
00:10:34.640 --> 00:10:35.840
No. nothing.

166
00:10:36.600 --> 00:10:38.160
-Okay. pet.
-Oh. hang on.

167
00:10:38.480 --> 00:10:42.120
Erm. I found this
further down the trail.

168
00:10:44.600 --> 00:10:46.080
How far down the trail?

169
00:10:46.679 --> 00:10:47.760
About 50 yards.

170
00:10:48.280 --> 00:10:50.960
Sorry. I put it in me pocket
and then...

171
00:10:51.880 --> 00:10:54.120
I realised and I just remembered.

172
00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:58.400
I mean. it could have been dropped
by anyone. right?

173
00:10:58.559 --> 00:11:01.120
Well. better late than never. love.

174
00:11:01.640 --> 00:11:03.800
-Thanks.
-Cheers.

175
00:11:06.120 --> 00:11:08.640
(Vera) Steph. we need into that
as soon as possible.

176
00:11:09.240 --> 00:11:11.160
This credit card was found
on the cover of the phone.

177
00:11:11.280 --> 00:11:13.559
Name's a "Mrs H A Rushden".

178
00:11:14.040 --> 00:11:15.920
-So. is she our deceased?
-I don't know.

179
00:11:16.040 --> 00:11:18.120
Get onto the bank
and find her details.

180
00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:20.280
Maybe we should go
back to your rambler again.

181
00:11:20.679 --> 00:11:23.160
I mean. do you really buy he just
forgot picking up the phone?

182
00:11:23.240 --> 00:11:24.480
Oh. he was rattled.

183
00:11:24.559 --> 00:11:27.559
It's not every day of the week
you find a dead body. Joe.

184
00:11:28.320 --> 00:11:29.520
Ah. but you're right.

185
00:11:29.880 --> 00:11:33.200
Kenny. er. chase up his movements
for yesterday

186
00:11:33.679 --> 00:11:35.400
and do a background check
while you're at it.

187
00:11:35.600 --> 00:11:36.840
-Yes. ma'am.
-Oh. and Kenny.

188
00:11:37.320 --> 00:11:40.200
get forensics to check
for any signs of a scuffle

189
00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:43.320
-up to 200 yards along the trail.
-Will do. ma'am.

190
00:11:44.280 --> 00:11:45.280
Ma'am.

191
00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:46.920
You're not into that already.
are you?

192
00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:48.240
Not past the face ID or passcode

193
00:11:48.320 --> 00:11:49.640
But there's medical information
here.

194
00:11:50.160 --> 00:11:51.640
So you can make emergency calls

195
00:11:51.720 --> 00:11:53.040
from a lock screen
by pressing here.

196
00:11:53.160 --> 00:11:55.000
but you can also fill in
medical information.

197
00:11:55.120 --> 00:11:56.760
I've done it on mine.
Accessed here.

198
00:11:57.440 --> 00:11:59.920
And according to this. the phone
belongs to a Gabi Fischer.

199
00:12:00.559 --> 00:12:03.679
Oh. so not your Mrs Rushden
on the credit card?

200
00:12:03.760 --> 00:12:06.559
No. but there's an emergency
contact down as Helen Rushden.

201
00:12:06.800 --> 00:12:09.160
So it might not be the deceased.
but could be next of kin.

202
00:12:09.960 --> 00:12:11.200
Call that number.

203
00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:12.960
Find an address.

204
00:12:13.040 --> 00:12:15.480
get uniform over there.
but tell them to act dumb

205
00:12:15.559 --> 00:12:16.960
until we arrive.

206
00:12:17.160 --> 00:12:18.559
-Well done. Steph.
-Ma'am.

207
00:12:18.840 --> 00:12:22.280
Are you coming?
Before I get blocked in.

208
00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:28.120
{\an8}-(brakes squealing)
-(birds chirping)

209
00:12:39.160 --> 00:12:40.320
(music fades)

210
00:12:43.800 --> 00:12:46.559
Helen Rushden's waiting.
She's very worked up. apparently.

211
00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:50.040
And her adult sons
just turned up too.

212
00:12:50.720 --> 00:12:51.720
Is something wrong?

213
00:12:51.960 --> 00:12:53.040
Well. this the Rushden's.

214
00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:56.160
You've got dad.
mam. son. and daughter.

215
00:12:56.400 --> 00:12:58.640
But that's not our deceased. is it?

216
00:12:59.480 --> 00:13:01.960
-So maybe she's an in-law?
-(Helen) What's going on now?

217
00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:06.040
-Who are you?
-Er. Mrs Rushden.

218
00:13:06.200 --> 00:13:09.160
I'm DCI Vera Stanhope.
And this is DS...

219
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:11.640
this is DI Joe Ashworth.

220
00:13:11.840 --> 00:13:13.800
(Helen) Will someone just please
tell me what's happening?

221
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.040
Is this about Gabi?

222
00:13:15.440 --> 00:13:16.559
You know Gabi Fischer?

223
00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:18.280
(Helen) Yeah. she lives here.

224
00:13:18.679 --> 00:13:20.120
Is she a family member?

225
00:13:20.240 --> 00:13:23.280
No. but she's been living with Mam
the last few months.

226
00:13:23.840 --> 00:13:25.920
(Vera) Then I think
we'd better all sit down. love.

227
00:13:26.040 --> 00:13:27.040
Just tell me.

228
00:13:28.360 --> 00:13:31.360
Well. we're here because
we found a mobile phone

229
00:13:31.440 --> 00:13:33.280
with emergency information on it.

230
00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:35.400
Is it Gabi's phone? Er...

231
00:13:36.080 --> 00:13:38.160
I got her to put all that in
when she got sick.

232
00:13:38.520 --> 00:13:40.320
-Sick?
-Yeah.

233
00:13:41.240 --> 00:13:42.360
She's got cancer.

234
00:13:45.120 --> 00:13:48.000
Now. where is she?

235
00:13:50.240 --> 00:13:53.960
Well. I'm afraid
we also found a body. love.

236
00:13:55.559 --> 00:13:56.559
Oh.

237
00:13:58.679 --> 00:13:59.760
No.

238
00:14:02.520 --> 00:14:03.520
No.

239
00:14:04.360 --> 00:14:06.160
-I'm sorry.
-(Helen) No.

240
00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:09.480
(sobs)

241
00:14:10.040 --> 00:14:11.800
She came into one of me shops.

242
00:14:12.679 --> 00:14:15.440
Five. six months ago.

243
00:14:16.720 --> 00:14:18.800
I own a chain of coffee places.

244
00:14:19.440 --> 00:14:22.200
"Grounded Out."
Jonathon runs them with me.

245
00:14:22.800 --> 00:14:25.000
Oh. aye. there's one
near my station.

246
00:14:25.080 --> 00:14:26.320
Aye. it looks lovely.

247
00:14:26.560 --> 00:14:29.720
(Jonathon) Mam grew it from just
the one place into seven branches.

248
00:14:31.280 --> 00:14:36.400
Well. I was in one and Gabi
appeared. looking upset.

249
00:14:37.680 --> 00:14:40.360
I've a daughter of similar age.
Fiona.

250
00:14:41.800 --> 00:14:47.200
Anyway. we got talking
and I just liked her straight away.

251
00:14:47.560 --> 00:14:50.680
But she was having money troubles.
sofa surfing.

252
00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:53.320
She just seemed vulnerable.

253
00:14:54.440 --> 00:14:56.720
-So I tried to help her.
-Go on. love.

254
00:14:57.000 --> 00:15:00.680
Well. she turned up regularly
and we became friends.

255
00:15:03.280 --> 00:15:04.280
Then she got...

256
00:15:05.080 --> 00:15:08.200
back pain.
Was it three months or so ago?

257
00:15:09.280 --> 00:15:13.200
She was getting breathless as well.
I made her get it checked out.

258
00:15:14.280 --> 00:15:18.320
Never imagining the diagnosis
would be Hodgkin Lymphoma.

259
00:15:21.840 --> 00:15:24.520
(Vera) So. is that when
she moved in here?

260
00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:26.920
(Helen) Gabi had every chance
of recovery

261
00:15:27.480 --> 00:15:29.080
if she was taken care of.

262
00:15:30.040 --> 00:15:32.240
We had the space.
Jonathon has his own family.

263
00:15:32.440 --> 00:15:33.600
Fiona had gone.

264
00:15:34.520 --> 00:15:36.360
And she was doing really well.

265
00:15:37.120 --> 00:15:39.960
Though... the chemo was tough.

266
00:15:41.320 --> 00:15:44.640
Made her tired and... and her hair.
she was...

267
00:15:45.880 --> 00:15:48.240
worried she'd have to shave it off
in the end.

268
00:15:50.760 --> 00:15:53.320
Why didn't she go
to her own family for help?

269
00:15:53.760 --> 00:15:57.880
They'd thrown her out. Abusive.
Emotionally. if not physically.

270
00:15:59.560 --> 00:16:00.640
When did you last see her?

271
00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:04.160
Yesterday. I dropped her
to the hospital for...

272
00:16:04.560 --> 00:16:06.760
1:30. then I saw a friend.

273
00:16:07.840 --> 00:16:10.600
I got a message saying
Gabi didn't need picking up.

274
00:16:11.360 --> 00:16:13.440
She needed space of her own
sometimes.

275
00:16:13.520 --> 00:16:16.560
and then when she didn't come home
at all.

276
00:16:17.120 --> 00:16:20.160
And you've no idea
why she was where we found her?

277
00:16:20.960 --> 00:16:22.640
No. None.

278
00:16:23.560 --> 00:16:25.840
-How about you. Mr Rushden?
-(Jonathon) No idea.

279
00:16:26.640 --> 00:16:29.680
I was at my place all day.
I didn't hear from her.

280
00:16:30.360 --> 00:16:33.160
And you don't know anyone
who might have wanted to harm her.

281
00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:34.720
(scoffs)

282
00:16:35.320 --> 00:16:38.200
Gabi was the sweetest. warmest...

283
00:16:39.920 --> 00:16:41.360
Who would want to hurt her?

284
00:16:43.200 --> 00:16:45.640
So. we still need to locate
and inform her next of kin.

285
00:16:45.720 --> 00:16:48.040
Aye. Not least to chat
about this "abuse."

286
00:16:48.120 --> 00:16:49.200
Excuse me.

287
00:16:50.560 --> 00:16:52.000
I just wanna let you know
that there's a...

288
00:16:52.120 --> 00:16:53.680
different perspective to me Mam's.

289
00:16:53.920 --> 00:16:55.320
-On Gabi?
-(Jonathon) Yeah.

290
00:16:55.680 --> 00:16:57.640
Look. Mam gave up a lot for her.

291
00:16:58.440 --> 00:16:59.840
Stepped back from work
and everything.

292
00:17:00.240 --> 00:17:01.880
But it drove a wedge
between her and Dad.

293
00:17:02.120 --> 00:17:05.760
-A wedge? What's that mean?
-Well. they're separated.

294
00:17:06.880 --> 00:17:08.240
Oh. because of Gabi?

295
00:17:08.320 --> 00:17:10.320
The attention she took.
Demanded.

296
00:17:11.520 --> 00:17:13.920
-There's no space left for Dad.
-So. he moved out?

297
00:17:14.080 --> 00:17:15.400
(Jonathon) Squeezed out. more like.

298
00:17:16.760 --> 00:17:17.840
Well. thanks. love.

299
00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:21.760
(dramatic music playing)

300
00:17:21.840 --> 00:17:24.400
Well. that is a different
perspective.

301
00:17:25.359 --> 00:17:26.800
-(music fades)
-Nice.

302
00:17:27.760 --> 00:17:29.160
This is good work. you know.

303
00:17:29.320 --> 00:17:30.359
(car approaching)

304
00:17:35.640 --> 00:17:36.840
(Tom) Lovely.

305
00:17:39.359 --> 00:17:41.680
She's in good condition.
What's wrong with her?

306
00:17:41.800 --> 00:17:43.880
-Nothing.
-(Joe) That's not why we're here.

307
00:17:44.480 --> 00:17:46.280
-Tom Rushden?
-Yes.

308
00:17:46.359 --> 00:17:48.000
Ah. DCI Stanhope.

309
00:17:48.440 --> 00:17:50.640
Now. is there somewhere
we can chat. love?

310
00:17:51.080 --> 00:17:52.520
(impact wrench whirring)

311
00:17:54.080 --> 00:17:55.960
Had you seen Gabi recently?

312
00:17:58.320 --> 00:17:59.359
No.

313
00:18:01.119 --> 00:18:02.440
Please. sorry. Sit down.

314
00:18:05.680 --> 00:18:08.520
Now. your son Jonathon suggested

315
00:18:08.640 --> 00:18:11.480
that there was no love lost
between you and her.

316
00:18:11.600 --> 00:18:12.960
Is that right?

317
00:18:13.960 --> 00:18:15.320
I guess that's fair enough.

318
00:18:15.800 --> 00:18:17.280
You hadn't liked her moving in.

319
00:18:17.520 --> 00:18:19.920
I hadn't liked her
and Helen. full stop.

320
00:18:20.359 --> 00:18:21.840
Things happened so quickly.

321
00:18:22.200 --> 00:18:24.920
They'd only just met
and were suddenly best friends.

322
00:18:25.359 --> 00:18:28.080
Then something more.
like mammy and daughter.

323
00:18:28.720 --> 00:18:32.080
And yes. Gabi was vulnerable.
then sick.

324
00:18:32.800 --> 00:18:35.320
But you can have cancer
and still be a leech.

325
00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:38.000
Oh. is that what you thought
she was. a leech?

326
00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:40.800
(Tom) Yeah. she fed off Helen.
Clung to her.

327
00:18:41.320 --> 00:18:43.720
Gabi moving in was supposed to be
temporary.

328
00:18:43.840 --> 00:18:46.200
-but once she was in...
-She wasn't going anywhere.

329
00:18:47.240 --> 00:18:48.560
If anyone was...

330
00:18:50.520 --> 00:18:51.520
was me.

331
00:18:51.880 --> 00:18:53.160
You really feel she pushed you out?

332
00:18:54.680 --> 00:18:57.520
Me and Helen
planned a night out once.

333
00:18:58.520 --> 00:18:59.960
Our anniversary.

334
00:19:00.920 --> 00:19:03.880
Suddenly. Gabi had breathing
difficulties.

335
00:19:04.359 --> 00:19:06.600
Then a full-blown panic attack.

336
00:19:07.920 --> 00:19:09.240
Helen felt she had to stay.

337
00:19:10.840 --> 00:19:14.119
I went on alone.
Had to get out of there.

338
00:19:15.080 --> 00:19:17.680
Why did your missus take her in
in the first place.

339
00:19:17.760 --> 00:19:18.840
give her so much?

340
00:19:18.960 --> 00:19:21.920
After Jonathon and Fiona.
we'd wanted another.

341
00:19:22.040 --> 00:19:24.760
but couldn't conceive.

342
00:19:25.640 --> 00:19:29.000
Maybe there was always a.
er. gap there.

343
00:19:29.640 --> 00:19:32.640
And Gabi lapped the mothering up.

344
00:19:33.240 --> 00:19:37.720
told Helen she made her feel safe.
part of the family.

345
00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:42.880
Ironically.
seeing as she was splitting one up.

346
00:19:47.080 --> 00:19:50.240
So where were you. love.
yesterday afternoon and evening?

347
00:19:51.359 --> 00:19:53.680
I was in the garage
till pretty late.

348
00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:57.760
-Were the mechanics with you?
-Well. yes. till 5:00 p.m.

349
00:19:58.840 --> 00:20:00.800
Then I ended the evening
back in here.

350
00:20:03.440 --> 00:20:05.480
Okay. love. Thanks for your time.

351
00:20:10.680 --> 00:20:11.720
(indistinct chatter)

352
00:20:11.800 --> 00:20:13.880
That collection of empties
he's got tells me

353
00:20:14.000 --> 00:20:15.680
he's not coping away from home.

354
00:20:15.880 --> 00:20:18.400
Aye. so this interloper's arrival
cost him a lot.

355
00:20:18.520 --> 00:20:19.520
Aye.

356
00:20:20.960 --> 00:20:23.720
Or did he win you over
by being nice about your car?

357
00:20:24.720 --> 00:20:26.080
I want his alibi checked.

358
00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:29.200
(Joe) Headache?

359
00:20:29.760 --> 00:20:32.400
I've got a grumbly tooth.
if you must know.

360
00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:35.560
Who is doing background checks
on the Rushdens?

361
00:20:35.800 --> 00:20:36.880
Mark.

362
00:20:37.280 --> 00:20:39.240
Well. let's see what that tells us.

363
00:20:39.400 --> 00:20:40.920
(car engine starts)

364
00:20:43.720 --> 00:20:46.200
Gabi Fischer. early twenties.

365
00:20:46.960 --> 00:20:49.800
Her body was found
near Fensham level crossing

366
00:20:49.880 --> 00:20:51.520
{\an8}this morning by a rambler.

367
00:20:51.800 --> 00:20:55.000
Now. we don't know
if this is murder yet.

368
00:20:55.080 --> 00:20:56.960
We're still waiting the results
of the post-mortem.

369
00:20:57.400 --> 00:20:59.960
But we are treating her death
as suspicious.

370
00:21:00.200 --> 00:21:02.800
Now. she'd been diagnosed
with Hodgkin Lymphoma.

371
00:21:02.920 --> 00:21:04.720
So. Steph.
get onto our hospital team

372
00:21:04.800 --> 00:21:06.440
and see if they can tell us
anything more.

373
00:21:07.160 --> 00:21:09.480
Now. where are we with her last
known movements?

374
00:21:09.600 --> 00:21:12.119
Nothing from door to door yet.
ma'am. but we're into her phone

375
00:21:12.200 --> 00:21:13.640
and I've been going through
call logs.

376
00:21:13.840 --> 00:21:16.720
Plus. I found a train app
with an e-ticket for yesterday.

377
00:21:17.760 --> 00:21:18.920
(Vera) Ah.

378
00:21:19.600 --> 00:21:21.040
So. how'd she pay for that?

379
00:21:21.160 --> 00:21:23.680
She used the credit card
we found inside the phone cover.

380
00:21:24.040 --> 00:21:27.720
And now Mrs Rushden said she
gave her that card for emergencies.

381
00:21:27.880 --> 00:21:30.560
-So what was the emergency?
-Where was the ticket to?

382
00:21:30.760 --> 00:21:32.080
Er. Bewton.

383
00:21:32.240 --> 00:21:34.440
-It's a small town. just...
-No. I know it.

384
00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:36.640
She'd have had to change trains.

385
00:21:37.240 --> 00:21:40.280
so she could have got off at Bewton
and hiked north.

386
00:21:40.520 --> 00:21:42.359
Then over the level crossing.

387
00:21:42.680 --> 00:21:46.600
Mark. we need the CCTV
from the train and the station.

388
00:21:46.760 --> 00:21:49.160
Let's try and pin her down.
see if anyone was with her.

389
00:21:49.280 --> 00:21:50.280
Ma'am.

390
00:21:50.400 --> 00:21:55.119
{\an8}Now. meanwhile. she'd been staying
under the auspices of Helen Rushden

391
00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:56.359
{\an8}in Newcastle.

392
00:21:56.560 --> 00:21:57.760
No relation.

393
00:21:57.920 --> 00:22:00.680
So. we still need to track down
her legal next of kin.

394
00:22:00.760 --> 00:22:03.920
-Mark. I want you on that too.
-Anything on the Rushdens. Mark?

395
00:22:04.240 --> 00:22:07.480
Er. yeah. there was one thing
on the estranged dad. Tom.

396
00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:09.880
{\an8}He had a previous conviction
for violent affray.

397
00:22:12.280 --> 00:22:15.600
-When was that?
-(Mark) Oh. way back. er. 1992.

398
00:22:16.080 --> 00:22:18.560
He got fined for it.
but no prison time.

399
00:22:18.680 --> 00:22:21.000
It was a drunken altercation
that got out of hand.

400
00:22:21.160 --> 00:22:22.160
(Vera) Okay.

401
00:22:22.320 --> 00:22:24.560
All the more reason
to check his alibi.

402
00:22:24.920 --> 00:22:27.320
Now. he said he was at the garage
with the other mechanics

403
00:22:27.400 --> 00:22:29.359
-till five. didn't he?
-Aye.

404
00:22:29.680 --> 00:22:32.240
Well. see if you can confirm
his whereabouts.

405
00:22:32.560 --> 00:22:35.320
And what about the sister.
Fiona Rushden?

406
00:22:35.400 --> 00:22:36.720
Has anyone made contact with her?

407
00:22:36.840 --> 00:22:40.800
She's overseas in Spain. ma'am.
Er. flew out yesterday evening.

408
00:22:41.800 --> 00:22:43.119
Did she now?

409
00:22:43.280 --> 00:22:46.480
Was that before or after Gabi
breathed her last?

410
00:22:46.600 --> 00:22:49.280
Erm. well. she was
on the 8:00 p.m. flight.

411
00:22:49.480 --> 00:22:52.280
but we don't know what time
exactly Gabi died. do we?

412
00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:55.040
Get a message to her. Mark.
We need her back here.

413
00:22:55.119 --> 00:22:57.480
(Steph) Er. I've one other thing
from Gabi's phone.

414
00:22:57.680 --> 00:23:00.240
The last person she rang
was Helen's son. Jonathan.

415
00:23:00.840 --> 00:23:02.160
Is that right?

416
00:23:02.720 --> 00:23:03.760
Just after 4:00 p.m.

417
00:23:03.880 --> 00:23:05.760
There were several missed calls
from him to her. too.

418
00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:07.600
from 5:20 or so.

419
00:23:08.040 --> 00:23:10.240
He told us he hadn't spoken
to Gabi all day.

420
00:23:10.359 --> 00:23:12.240
Aye. he did say that.

421
00:23:13.000 --> 00:23:15.160
(dramatic music playing)

422
00:23:24.760 --> 00:23:26.000
(music fades)

423
00:23:32.520 --> 00:23:36.200
Ah. good morning. Mr Rushden.
Thanks for meeting with us.

424
00:23:36.320 --> 00:23:38.920
DCI Stanhope.
This is Freya. my wife.

425
00:23:39.080 --> 00:23:40.840
-(Vera) Hello. love.
-(Joe) And who's this?

426
00:23:41.119 --> 00:23:43.119
(Jonathon) This is my boy.
Say hello. Jack.

427
00:23:43.240 --> 00:23:44.280
Hello.

428
00:23:44.440 --> 00:23:46.560
(Jonathon) Jack likes to call by
when we meet branch managers.

429
00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:49.119
Steals a pastry. Er...

430
00:23:49.920 --> 00:23:51.840
DCI Stanhope's here
to talk about Gabi.

431
00:23:52.880 --> 00:23:55.480
That poor girl. So awful.

432
00:23:56.960 --> 00:23:59.520
Come on. mister. (chuckles)
Park time.

433
00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:02.080
(sighs) Shall we take this inside?

434
00:24:06.840 --> 00:24:07.880
Cheers.

435
00:24:08.640 --> 00:24:09.800
So?

436
00:24:11.000 --> 00:24:12.280
How exactly can I help?

437
00:24:12.760 --> 00:24:15.520
Well. you didn't mention Gabi
calling you the day she died.

438
00:24:16.480 --> 00:24:18.080
(Vera) About 4:00 p.m.. love.

439
00:24:18.560 --> 00:24:20.840
Which means. as far as we know.

440
00:24:20.920 --> 00:24:23.480
you were the last person
to have spoken to her.

441
00:24:23.840 --> 00:24:25.880
(Jonathon) She called at 4:00?

442
00:24:26.040 --> 00:24:27.880
-Couldn't have been important.
-No.

443
00:24:28.320 --> 00:24:30.600
When your mam was frantic
about her going missing.

444
00:24:31.000 --> 00:24:32.600
Well. we didn't know
she was missing then.

445
00:24:33.040 --> 00:24:35.560
And we weren't worried
till later. (sighs)

446
00:24:36.040 --> 00:24:37.600
Gabi passed on little messages
all the time.

447
00:24:37.840 --> 00:24:38.960
About what?

448
00:24:39.359 --> 00:24:41.200
I think it might have been
something about this weekend.

449
00:24:41.800 --> 00:24:43.160
Me and Freya
coming to Mam's for dinner.

450
00:24:44.280 --> 00:24:47.320
Well. she called you about that.
from the middle of the countryside.

451
00:24:47.480 --> 00:24:48.720
I didn't know where she was.

452
00:24:49.320 --> 00:24:51.920
And I mean. later.
when Mam got worried.

453
00:24:52.200 --> 00:24:55.040
I said I'd try and track Gabi down.
So I phoned her.

454
00:24:55.160 --> 00:24:57.119
Yeah. we know about those calls
as well. love.

455
00:24:57.320 --> 00:24:59.080
Which you also didn't mention.

456
00:24:59.680 --> 00:25:01.960
Hmm. Well. she didn't answer.

457
00:25:03.240 --> 00:25:04.240
So I didn't talk to her.

458
00:25:05.440 --> 00:25:08.000
Now. you said you were at home
yesterday.

459
00:25:11.119 --> 00:25:12.119
That's right.

460
00:25:13.240 --> 00:25:15.480
-Working.
-All day?

461
00:25:15.800 --> 00:25:18.119
I think I went for a walk
around the block at lunchtime.

462
00:25:19.480 --> 00:25:20.920
Can anyone confirm where you were?

463
00:25:21.720 --> 00:25:23.800
Hmm. Freya.

464
00:25:24.320 --> 00:25:26.720
Jack had nursery day.
She was around.

465
00:25:27.280 --> 00:25:28.960
Except for drop-off and pick-up.

466
00:25:30.280 --> 00:25:32.240
-(tooth cracking)
-(groans. gasps)

467
00:25:32.920 --> 00:25:38.440
(whimsical music playing. fades)

468
00:25:40.720 --> 00:25:43.400
Mark? Any news on the train?

469
00:25:43.800 --> 00:25:46.720
Er. yeah. I've got her on the train
CCTV

470
00:25:46.840 --> 00:25:48.280
from Newcastle to Bewton.

471
00:25:48.359 --> 00:25:51.640
Er. she's by herself.
disembarks at 3:32

472
00:25:51.760 --> 00:25:53.040
and then we lose her.

473
00:25:53.160 --> 00:25:56.160
Er. I also checked to see
if anyone phoned

474
00:25:56.240 --> 00:25:57.600
to use the Fensham level crossing.

475
00:25:57.760 --> 00:25:59.520
-(Joe) Good thinking.
-(Vera) And?

476
00:25:59.960 --> 00:26:02.160
Er. yeah.
they said there was a call.

477
00:26:02.359 --> 00:26:05.280
Sounded like a young woman
at 4:28 p.m.

478
00:26:05.520 --> 00:26:07.000
Well. if that was Gabi.

479
00:26:07.080 --> 00:26:08.920
we'd have been right
about her journey.

480
00:26:09.119 --> 00:26:10.800
It's about an hour's hike

481
00:26:11.160 --> 00:26:14.880
north from Bewton.
over the level crossing.

482
00:26:16.440 --> 00:26:19.840
But where was she heading?
What was she doing there?

483
00:26:20.359 --> 00:26:21.800
Maybe she agreed
to meet her attacker.

484
00:26:21.920 --> 00:26:23.280
They could have walked together.

485
00:26:24.280 --> 00:26:25.280
Hmm...

486
00:26:25.920 --> 00:26:27.960
Did anyone else call the signalman?

487
00:26:28.040 --> 00:26:29.160
No. ma'am.

488
00:26:29.880 --> 00:26:31.640
Okay. so let's work backwards.

489
00:26:32.160 --> 00:26:34.560
See if you can pick her up on CCTV

490
00:26:34.720 --> 00:26:37.320
before she gets on the train
at Newcastle.

491
00:26:38.640 --> 00:26:41.080
(Joe) Steph.
any more on Gabi's phone?

492
00:26:41.240 --> 00:26:42.440
Er. not much.

493
00:26:42.560 --> 00:26:45.520
The phone itself was a gift a few
months back from Helen Rushden.

494
00:26:45.680 --> 00:26:47.560
Gabi mainly called
and messaged Helen.

495
00:26:48.640 --> 00:26:50.760
(Vera) Don't you find that odd.
Steph?

496
00:26:51.400 --> 00:26:55.040
A 20-something lass only calling
her substitute mam.

497
00:26:55.640 --> 00:26:56.960
Hasn't she got any mates?

498
00:26:57.080 --> 00:26:59.119
Er. there's a handful
of other contacts to go through.

499
00:26:59.320 --> 00:27:00.880
Yeah. well. make sure you do.

500
00:27:01.080 --> 00:27:04.320
She's no real social media profile
to speak of either. ma'am.

501
00:27:05.720 --> 00:27:07.280
In this day and age...

502
00:27:09.080 --> 00:27:12.440
Mark. how are you doing
tracing her next of kin?

503
00:27:12.520 --> 00:27:15.119
(sighs) Not great. ma'am.
It's strange. though.

504
00:27:15.200 --> 00:27:17.640
I can't find a birth record
for a Gabi Fischer.

505
00:27:18.080 --> 00:27:20.800
Er. not one that matches
the birthday that Helen gave us.

506
00:27:20.920 --> 00:27:22.359
-You what?
-Er. I've tried

507
00:27:22.480 --> 00:27:23.920
Gabrielle. Gabriella...

508
00:27:24.200 --> 00:27:25.200
So what are you saying.

509
00:27:25.280 --> 00:27:27.320
this Gabi Fischer's
an assumed identity?

510
00:27:27.520 --> 00:27:28.520
Now. how does that work?

511
00:27:28.600 --> 00:27:31.200
How does she go anywhere.
do anything. buy anything?

512
00:27:31.440 --> 00:27:33.440
Well. it sounds like
Helen paid for most of it.

513
00:27:33.560 --> 00:27:34.600
Hmm.

514
00:27:36.040 --> 00:27:37.760
(clicks tongue) Okay. Mark.

515
00:27:37.840 --> 00:27:40.359
get on to missing persons.
forget her name.

516
00:27:40.720 --> 00:27:44.320
and see if you can match
her details to any unsolved cases.

517
00:27:44.880 --> 00:27:46.440
That's going to be a lot of people.
ma'am.

518
00:27:46.520 --> 00:27:48.040
Yeah. well.
you'd better get on with it. then.

519
00:27:48.240 --> 00:27:49.440
That was the morgue.

520
00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:52.760
At last. some solid evidence.

521
00:27:52.960 --> 00:27:55.240
-(thuds)
-(Vera) You coming or what?

522
00:28:01.760 --> 00:28:03.680
Vera. I hear we're not sure

523
00:28:03.760 --> 00:28:05.240
what name to put
on the paperwork yet.

524
00:28:05.680 --> 00:28:07.560
Does that change what she died of?

525
00:28:07.840 --> 00:28:10.800
I suppose not.
I mentioned asphyxiation.

526
00:28:10.920 --> 00:28:12.720
-Aye.
-But not from being strangled.

527
00:28:12.840 --> 00:28:14.000
I was wrong anyway.

528
00:28:14.080 --> 00:28:16.760
It was a massive thrombotic
occlusion of the basilar artery.

529
00:28:16.920 --> 00:28:17.920
A blood clot?

530
00:28:18.200 --> 00:28:20.520
One that stopped the blood flow
to her brain. yes.

531
00:28:21.560 --> 00:28:24.480
-Caused by what?
-A whiplash-like injury.

532
00:28:24.720 --> 00:28:27.680
There's a microscopic lesion
of the right vertebral artery

533
00:28:27.840 --> 00:28:29.880
on the atlantoaxial joint
in the neck.

534
00:28:30.560 --> 00:28:32.240
So I'm guessing there was a fight.

535
00:28:32.640 --> 00:28:35.760
Er. she was grabbed. shaken.
and pushed backwards.

536
00:28:36.119 --> 00:28:38.200
She fell and landed on something.
which bruised her.

537
00:28:38.320 --> 00:28:39.400
and more importantly.

538
00:28:39.480 --> 00:28:41.080
jerked her head back.
causing the lesion.

539
00:28:41.840 --> 00:28:43.720
And that maps with the surroundings
where we found her?

540
00:28:43.960 --> 00:28:45.560
Mm-hmm. Correct. DI Ashworth.

541
00:28:45.880 --> 00:28:48.200
There's tree stumps
that she more than likely fell on.

542
00:28:49.320 --> 00:28:51.160
(sighs) Okay. Thanks. Paula.

543
00:28:51.880 --> 00:28:55.360
Just one last thing to mention.
The deceased cancer diagnosis.

544
00:28:55.560 --> 00:28:56.960
Hodgkin's Lymphoma.

545
00:28:57.080 --> 00:28:59.240
I found no evidence
for chemo treatment.

546
00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:03.040
No implanted central line.
no marks from a cannula site.

547
00:29:03.160 --> 00:29:06.120
-Oh.
-So she wasn't receiving treatment?

548
00:29:06.600 --> 00:29:08.720
She was thin.
but I think through dieting.

549
00:29:09.040 --> 00:29:10.760
And she also had
rather heavy makeup on.

550
00:29:10.880 --> 00:29:13.520
which made her look pale.
And see here.

551
00:29:15.000 --> 00:29:16.000
Oh...

552
00:29:18.360 --> 00:29:20.800
The hair's been cut
a few points close to the roots.

553
00:29:21.120 --> 00:29:23.720
so when pulled or brushed.
it would come loose.

554
00:29:24.920 --> 00:29:26.640
As if it was fallen out.

555
00:29:27.000 --> 00:29:29.480
I've confirmed with blood results
and a biopsy.

556
00:29:29.920 --> 00:29:32.080
this young woman
didn't have cancer.

557
00:29:32.400 --> 00:29:33.520
She'd never had cancer.

558
00:29:34.360 --> 00:29:36.800
-She was faking it?
-(Paula) Hmm.

559
00:29:37.600 --> 00:29:39.760
(tense music playing)

560
00:29:42.280 --> 00:29:43.360
(music fades)

561
00:29:43.520 --> 00:29:45.720
(Vera) You had no clue
she'd been lying to you?

562
00:29:45.840 --> 00:29:48.440
I took her to the hospital
for treatment.

563
00:29:48.640 --> 00:29:50.480
I can show you doctor's letters.

564
00:29:50.680 --> 00:29:52.440
She put me in touch
with her cancer nurse.

565
00:29:52.520 --> 00:29:53.520
for God's sakes.

566
00:29:54.080 --> 00:29:56.720
Danni. She was called Danni Verma.

567
00:29:56.840 --> 00:29:58.720
You never went with her
to one of her appointments

568
00:29:58.800 --> 00:30:00.600
-or treatment sessions?
-Well. I offered.

569
00:30:00.680 --> 00:30:02.880
She didn't want me to see
that stuff going into her.

570
00:30:03.000 --> 00:30:06.040
There was no diagnosis. love.

571
00:30:07.640 --> 00:30:10.200
No. No treatments.

572
00:30:10.800 --> 00:30:11.800
No.

573
00:30:13.360 --> 00:30:14.520
(gasps)

574
00:30:17.360 --> 00:30:19.880
What kind of person
lies about that?

575
00:30:20.800 --> 00:30:23.400
(pensive music playing)

576
00:30:33.760 --> 00:30:34.760
How is she?

577
00:30:35.560 --> 00:30:38.280
Family liaisons with her.
This Gabi's room?

578
00:30:38.800 --> 00:30:41.000
Well. it was the daughter's.
Fiona's.

579
00:30:41.080 --> 00:30:43.760
but she's been relegated
to the bottom drawer.

580
00:30:45.120 --> 00:30:49.160
And we still know nothing about
this lass who's replaced her.

581
00:30:50.120 --> 00:30:52.920
Well. Fiona's flying back tomorrow.
so maybe that'll give us something.

582
00:30:53.040 --> 00:30:54.240
(Vera) Right.

583
00:30:56.720 --> 00:30:57.760
Hey. hold on.

584
00:30:59.520 --> 00:31:00.600
Can you pull that out?

585
00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:03.160
(Joe grunts)

586
00:31:11.600 --> 00:31:13.080
What the hell is that?

587
00:31:18.440 --> 00:31:22.360
(Vera) And on top of all this.
our Gabi was good at DIY.

588
00:31:23.160 --> 00:31:25.000
What have we got on this lot
so far. Mark?

589
00:31:25.320 --> 00:31:28.320
Well. first look at the laptop
already shows

590
00:31:28.480 --> 00:31:31.680
forged medical letters
and several fake email accounts.

591
00:31:32.120 --> 00:31:35.520
And online activity
includes bookmarked pages

592
00:31:35.600 --> 00:31:38.480
about cancer symptoms
and support groups.

593
00:31:38.640 --> 00:31:40.320
And what about the phones
and the SIM cards?

594
00:31:40.520 --> 00:31:43.520
Er. each SIM has letters
written on. like DV on this one.

595
00:31:44.000 --> 00:31:47.080
And the texts from this card
pretend to be from a Danni Verma.

596
00:31:47.600 --> 00:31:51.360
Ah. now. she told Helen
Danni Verma was her cancer nurse.

597
00:31:51.520 --> 00:31:53.120
Well. I'll carry on
going through the SIM's.

598
00:31:54.080 --> 00:31:55.200
What about the drugs?

599
00:31:55.360 --> 00:31:57.600
(Joe) Well. they're still
at the lab. but early testing

600
00:31:57.760 --> 00:31:59.840
would suggest that
that bag was full of ketamine.

601
00:32:00.080 --> 00:32:02.760
Well. our toxicologist said there
was nothing in her system.

602
00:32:03.160 --> 00:32:05.480
So. holding them
for someone else. then?

603
00:32:06.080 --> 00:32:07.320
Could have been selling them.

604
00:32:07.520 --> 00:32:09.560
I've sent a picture of Gabi
to the hospital.

605
00:32:09.880 --> 00:32:12.000
-And?
-I was gonna follow up in person.

606
00:32:12.080 --> 00:32:13.800
I'll take Kenny with us.
if you can spare us.

607
00:32:14.040 --> 00:32:15.440
(sighs) I'll manage.

608
00:32:15.760 --> 00:32:17.600
Even if it's just to check
the CCTV?

609
00:32:17.840 --> 00:32:20.360
And see if you can find out
exactly what she did

610
00:32:20.440 --> 00:32:23.080
after Helen left her there
for treatment.

611
00:32:25.840 --> 00:32:30.320
Meanwhile. I have the unenviable
task of informing her next of kin.

612
00:32:31.080 --> 00:32:36.000
Maybe find out
who Gabrielle McSwain really was.

613
00:32:37.840 --> 00:32:41.320
(sombre music playing)

614
00:32:49.880 --> 00:32:52.640
(seagulls screeching)

615
00:33:17.440 --> 00:33:19.520
-(engine sputtering)
-(keys rattling)

616
00:33:23.320 --> 00:33:25.000
(sombre music fades out)

617
00:33:26.600 --> 00:33:29.320
(tense music playing)

618
00:33:46.320 --> 00:33:47.960
(doorbell ringing)

619
00:33:49.440 --> 00:33:54.280
(sobs)

620
00:33:57.880 --> 00:33:59.600
When did Gabi leave home?

621
00:34:01.000 --> 00:34:06.280
(sighs)
Er. must be six months ago.

622
00:34:08.840 --> 00:34:10.520
She didn't tell us
where she was going.

623
00:34:11.320 --> 00:34:12.560
She never got in touch.

624
00:34:13.080 --> 00:34:16.239
And you didn't look for her.
report her missing?

625
00:34:18.280 --> 00:34:19.280
Only...

626
00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:26.960
she'd suggested that something
had happened here at home.

627
00:34:28.640 --> 00:34:30.680
Hinted at abuse.

628
00:34:32.840 --> 00:34:33.840
Abuse?

629
00:34:36.360 --> 00:34:37.360
Gabi lied.

630
00:34:38.239 --> 00:34:40.520
Okay? She lied all the time.

631
00:34:41.280 --> 00:34:42.400
So when she left...

632
00:34:45.480 --> 00:34:47.160
Gabi was our daughter
and we loved her.

633
00:34:47.280 --> 00:34:48.280
but when she went...

634
00:34:49.600 --> 00:34:51.600
in some ways. it was a relief.

635
00:34:52.280 --> 00:34:54.960
-Not that she was always...
-No. no.

636
00:34:55.040 --> 00:34:57.719
She was happy when she was younger.

637
00:34:58.320 --> 00:34:59.600
So what changed?

638
00:35:04.920 --> 00:35:06.320
Her little sister got ill.

639
00:35:08.960 --> 00:35:10.400
Gabi has a sister?

640
00:35:11.080 --> 00:35:12.080
Emma.

641
00:35:13.840 --> 00:35:14.840
She died.

642
00:35:16.280 --> 00:35:19.760
(sighs) I am so sorry.

643
00:35:20.640 --> 00:35:21.640
Cancer.

644
00:35:21.840 --> 00:35:23.960
(breathes deeply) She was 16.

645
00:35:26.280 --> 00:35:27.800
And that took...

646
00:35:29.280 --> 00:35:30.880
...so much attention.

647
00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:35.880
(Matthew) Gabi started
to get into trouble at school.

648
00:35:38.920 --> 00:35:40.560
Continued after she left.

649
00:35:42.920 --> 00:35:43.920
Acting out.

650
00:35:44.600 --> 00:35:45.920
She took money from us.

651
00:35:47.080 --> 00:35:48.320
Petty thefts around town.

652
00:35:50.080 --> 00:35:51.280
We tried to help.

653
00:35:53.440 --> 00:35:56.120
I got a referral
to a child psychologist

654
00:35:56.320 --> 00:35:57.320
and everything.

655
00:35:58.080 --> 00:36:00.160
(Vera) There's something else
I need to tell you.

656
00:36:01.520 --> 00:36:06.080
Gabi had been pretending to be ill
with Hodgkin Lymphoma.

657
00:36:06.640 --> 00:36:08.120
What?

658
00:36:09.560 --> 00:36:10.560
No.

659
00:36:11.160 --> 00:36:13.000
(cries) No. No.

660
00:36:13.680 --> 00:36:15.719
No. No.

661
00:36:16.239 --> 00:36:17.320
That's what Emma had.

662
00:36:17.560 --> 00:36:21.600
(Deborah sobs)

663
00:36:21.920 --> 00:36:25.120
I'm sorry.
I'm going to have to ask you.

664
00:36:26.960 --> 00:36:30.200
Where were you both
on Wednesday afternoon?

665
00:36:30.800 --> 00:36:32.320
Debs was on a shift.

666
00:36:33.080 --> 00:36:34.280
The Locks Nursing Home

667
00:36:34.400 --> 00:36:36.600
and Matthew would have been
out on the water.

668
00:36:36.719 --> 00:36:39.680
I... I rent a pontoon boat
out of the harbour.

669
00:36:40.920 --> 00:36:41.920
Okay.

670
00:36:43.680 --> 00:36:47.560
Thanks for your time.
It's much appreciated.

671
00:36:55.320 --> 00:36:56.560
(cries)

672
00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:01.280
You do oncology. I'll do CCTV.

673
00:37:01.880 --> 00:37:03.920
Ah. sounds good to me. sir.

674
00:37:05.120 --> 00:37:06.840
Joe's probably fine. Eh. Ken?

675
00:37:11.160 --> 00:37:13.760
Thanks for sparing so much time.
Maia. I know it can be tedious.

676
00:37:13.920 --> 00:37:15.080
Ah. no problem.

677
00:37:15.160 --> 00:37:16.760
So we know she was a regular
at the cafe.

678
00:37:16.840 --> 00:37:18.640
but do we know who that is
sat next to her?

679
00:37:18.880 --> 00:37:20.040
(Maia) Oh. sorry.

680
00:37:20.760 --> 00:37:23.239
There's 4.000 employees
at this hospital.

681
00:37:23.760 --> 00:37:27.040
However. white coat does mean
medical staff. though.

682
00:37:27.280 --> 00:37:28.520
It should narrow it down.

683
00:37:28.719 --> 00:37:29.719
Okay. great.

684
00:37:29.840 --> 00:37:31.280
Can I get all this footage
sent over?

685
00:37:31.480 --> 00:37:33.440
-(Maia) Sure. Anything you want.
-(mobile phone buzzing)

686
00:37:33.640 --> 00:37:35.280
Excuse me. Boss?

687
00:37:36.920 --> 00:37:38.320
How did you get on with the family?

688
00:37:38.440 --> 00:37:39.880
Well. wait for it.

689
00:37:40.440 --> 00:37:43.360
She had a younger sister
who died of cancer.

690
00:37:43.440 --> 00:37:44.640
You're kidding.

691
00:37:44.760 --> 00:37:46.239
(Vera) Ah.
you couldn't make it up.

692
00:37:46.640 --> 00:37:49.360
And they painted Gabi
as being involved in all sorts.

693
00:37:49.440 --> 00:37:51.880
compulsive. liar. petty theft.

694
00:37:52.520 --> 00:37:55.360
-(Joe) And the abuse?
-Denied it. Said she'd lied.

695
00:37:55.480 --> 00:37:57.160
Well. they would do.

696
00:37:57.520 --> 00:37:59.880
Could some kind of trouble
have followed her to Newcastle?

697
00:37:59.960 --> 00:38:02.120
(Vera) Well. let's do some digging.

698
00:38:02.440 --> 00:38:06.400
But then if a family had already
lost one daughter.

699
00:38:07.360 --> 00:38:09.960
wouldn't they go
chasing after the other one.

700
00:38:10.080 --> 00:38:12.120
no matter how much
you've been acting up?

701
00:38:12.600 --> 00:38:14.000
(Joe) You think they're hiding
something?

702
00:38:15.920 --> 00:38:17.680
I'll see you back at the station.

703
00:38:21.480 --> 00:38:22.600
Has she got more abrasive?

704
00:38:23.440 --> 00:38:24.640
The boss. I mean.

705
00:38:25.440 --> 00:38:26.719
Well. er...

706
00:38:27.680 --> 00:38:30.280
I think it's more like
your memories are rose-tinted. eh?

707
00:38:30.440 --> 00:38:33.040
Look. she's the best.
We all know that. That's fine.

708
00:38:33.640 --> 00:38:36.160
But I'm ambitious. you know?
I want a team of my own one day.

709
00:38:36.800 --> 00:38:38.760
She makes it feel
like I've just been demoted.

710
00:38:39.880 --> 00:38:41.040
Join the club. mate.

711
00:38:41.840 --> 00:38:44.040
My advice is.
don't take it personally.

712
00:38:44.600 --> 00:38:47.560
(dramatic music playing)

713
00:38:51.960 --> 00:38:54.320
(Joe) Well. perhaps we can jog
your memory. Miss Adeyemi?

714
00:38:56.200 --> 00:38:57.560
Oh. Gabi.

715
00:38:58.520 --> 00:39:00.280
Yeah. I know who you mean now.

716
00:39:00.960 --> 00:39:03.480
-She's really dead?
-We're afraid so.

717
00:39:03.560 --> 00:39:05.600
But she seemed to be doing so well.

718
00:39:05.880 --> 00:39:07.520
Well. still in early treatment.

719
00:39:08.080 --> 00:39:09.360
You mean the chemo?

720
00:39:09.719 --> 00:39:14.040
Yeah. Well. did the lymphoma.
were there complications?

721
00:39:14.280 --> 00:39:16.160
Oh. the cancer didn't kill her.

722
00:39:16.600 --> 00:39:18.239
I mean. we'd hardly be here
if it had.

723
00:39:19.200 --> 00:39:21.080
We're treating her death
as suspicious.

724
00:39:21.560 --> 00:39:22.560
What?

725
00:39:23.400 --> 00:39:24.400
What happened to her?

726
00:39:24.680 --> 00:39:26.160
That's what
we're trying to find out.

727
00:39:26.719 --> 00:39:28.120
The one thing we did discover

728
00:39:28.600 --> 00:39:30.360
is that Gabi
didn't really have cancer.

729
00:39:31.280 --> 00:39:32.320
But...

730
00:39:32.800 --> 00:39:37.080
No. We'd talk about her symptoms.
Or the side effects of her drugs.

731
00:39:37.480 --> 00:39:39.880
Did you help Gabi
fabricate her condition?

732
00:39:39.960 --> 00:39:41.160
Of course not.

733
00:39:41.320 --> 00:39:43.719
So. the contact you had with her
was more accidental then?

734
00:39:44.040 --> 00:39:46.200
-A casual thing?
-(Rosa) Yes.

735
00:39:47.280 --> 00:39:49.520
Look. I'm a bit in shock here.
to be honest.

736
00:39:50.239 --> 00:39:52.080
I'm sorry I can't be of more help.

737
00:39:53.400 --> 00:39:54.960
Well. there's nothing else
I can tell you.

738
00:39:56.480 --> 00:39:57.480
Okay.

739
00:39:58.480 --> 00:39:59.840
Well. thanks for your time. anyway.

740
00:40:00.480 --> 00:40:01.719
Thank you.

741
00:40:08.840 --> 00:40:09.840
Ma'am.

742
00:40:09.920 --> 00:40:11.360
(Vera) What's this.
a welcoming committee?

743
00:40:11.600 --> 00:40:13.600
In that case. someone get us a tea.

744
00:40:13.719 --> 00:40:14.719
Ma'am. I've been working

745
00:40:14.800 --> 00:40:16.320
through all of Gabi's
pay-as-you-go cards.

746
00:40:16.520 --> 00:40:17.520
And?

747
00:40:17.600 --> 00:40:18.920
The SIM that was in
her hidden phone

748
00:40:19.000 --> 00:40:20.640
seems different of the others
used for her con.

749
00:40:20.760 --> 00:40:22.640
It isn't labelled
with any initials.

750
00:40:22.719 --> 00:40:26.320
but there was frequent calls
to a number called LC.

751
00:40:26.560 --> 00:40:30.600
So she was making regular calls
to somebody besides Helen.

752
00:40:30.760 --> 00:40:32.440
So who is this LC?

753
00:40:32.600 --> 00:40:34.080
(Mark) Er. well. bear with us.
ma'am.

754
00:40:34.200 --> 00:40:35.840
but I've been tracking Gabi
backwards

755
00:40:35.920 --> 00:40:37.160
from when she got on the train.

756
00:40:37.520 --> 00:40:40.239
Er. now. she's alone
at the station.

757
00:40:40.560 --> 00:40:43.400
but then on the street CCTV
outside.

758
00:40:43.560 --> 00:40:45.480
we've caught her arguing
with a young male.

759
00:40:46.840 --> 00:40:49.120
-What?
-Yeah. here's the footage.

760
00:40:52.719 --> 00:40:55.000
(Vera) And this is who you think
she's been calling?

761
00:40:55.680 --> 00:40:56.760
Why do you think that?

762
00:40:56.960 --> 00:40:58.800
Because I traced
the unknown phone number.

763
00:40:58.960 --> 00:41:00.400
and it's not a pay-as-you-go.

764
00:41:00.640 --> 00:41:03.080
It's a contract in the name
of Lee Critchley.

765
00:41:03.520 --> 00:41:04.680
LC.

766
00:41:04.760 --> 00:41:07.880
Yeah. and he's on the radar
for low-level drug dealing.

767
00:41:08.280 --> 00:41:11.840
Well. that sounds like our lad.
Well done. the pair of you.

768
00:41:12.320 --> 00:41:14.600
Now. cancel that tea. call Joe.

769
00:41:14.760 --> 00:41:17.080
give him that address.
tell him to meet us there.

770
00:41:17.719 --> 00:41:18.719
-Ma'am.
-Ma'am.

771
00:41:19.360 --> 00:41:22.120
(birds screeching)

772
00:41:28.480 --> 00:41:31.920
-The hospital pharmacist.
-Aye. Rosa Adeyemi.

773
00:41:32.480 --> 00:41:33.680
She seemed nervy.

774
00:41:33.800 --> 00:41:36.280
Kenny's going to ask some discreet
questions about her.

775
00:41:36.719 --> 00:41:39.239
Oh. your flavour of the month then
with Kenny again.

776
00:41:39.320 --> 00:41:42.400
-You what?
-Now you've stopped assessing us.

777
00:41:43.560 --> 00:41:45.520
We'll run a background check
on her and all.

778
00:41:46.719 --> 00:41:49.160
(indistinct chatter)

779
00:41:53.960 --> 00:41:56.880
Did you ask this Rosa
about the ketamine Gabi had?

780
00:41:57.239 --> 00:41:58.600
Why. you want some
for your toothache?

781
00:41:58.760 --> 00:42:02.040
(clicks tongue. sighs)

782
00:42:02.440 --> 00:42:03.520
(door knocking)

783
00:42:07.920 --> 00:42:11.200
Hello. love. Is Lee Critchley home?

784
00:42:11.520 --> 00:42:13.880
-(Sian) No.
-That's a shame.

785
00:42:14.960 --> 00:42:15.960
You family?

786
00:42:16.640 --> 00:42:19.040
-His girlfriend.
-Ah. quick chat then.

787
00:42:21.640 --> 00:42:24.120
Hey. no need to tidy up for us.
pet.

788
00:42:24.440 --> 00:42:26.120
We're not searching the place.

789
00:42:26.960 --> 00:42:28.000
Today.

790
00:42:28.560 --> 00:42:30.120
Lee's not answering me messages.

791
00:42:30.360 --> 00:42:31.360
Has something happened?

792
00:42:31.680 --> 00:42:34.680
We're here cos of Gabi Fischer.
also known as Gabi McSwain.

793
00:42:35.360 --> 00:42:37.880
-What about her?
-Well. she's dead. pet.

794
00:42:38.200 --> 00:42:39.960
Killed three days ago.

795
00:42:41.080 --> 00:42:42.080
What?

796
00:42:42.200 --> 00:42:44.280
And she was seen with Lee earlier
the same day.

797
00:42:46.480 --> 00:42:47.480
Er...

798
00:42:49.160 --> 00:42:52.800
Gabi crashed here for a bit.
months back.

799
00:42:53.040 --> 00:42:54.960
Lee knew her from where he grew up.

800
00:42:55.239 --> 00:42:58.040
So. she was what.
a past girlfriend?

801
00:43:00.000 --> 00:43:02.920
Eh. that wouldn't have been
very nice. love.

802
00:43:03.080 --> 00:43:05.560
having his ex
sleeping in the spare room.

803
00:43:06.320 --> 00:43:09.320
So what. did she start cosying up
to your boyfriend again?

804
00:43:09.840 --> 00:43:12.760
Gabi would cosy up to anyone
to get what she wanted.

805
00:43:13.360 --> 00:43:14.400
What does that mean?

806
00:43:15.280 --> 00:43:19.160
(sighs) She outstayed her welcome.
I wanted her gone.

807
00:43:20.160 --> 00:43:22.920
Then suddenly she was all over me.

808
00:43:23.000 --> 00:43:26.320
telling me how amazing I am.
how Lee's lucky to have us.

809
00:43:27.280 --> 00:43:29.200
And then I found text messages
from her.

810
00:43:29.320 --> 00:43:30.719
calling me a stupid bitch.

811
00:43:31.920 --> 00:43:34.640
-So. you were glad when she left?
-Yeah.

812
00:43:36.200 --> 00:43:39.640
But they were still in touch.
I found a text from her last week.

813
00:43:41.680 --> 00:43:43.840
Do you go through his phone
regularly. do you?

814
00:43:46.040 --> 00:43:51.640
I got angry. asked him about it.
and he was raging.

815
00:43:52.880 --> 00:43:57.440
But this was. it was more her
he was angry with.

816
00:43:57.640 --> 00:43:59.440
He was angry at Gabi?

817
00:44:00.760 --> 00:44:01.760
Why?

818
00:44:02.000 --> 00:44:05.120
(dramatic music playing)

819
00:44:07.360 --> 00:44:10.080
(Vera) We've got a drug dealer.
a pharmacist.

820
00:44:10.200 --> 00:44:13.480
and the deceased.
who was skilled at deception

821
00:44:13.760 --> 00:44:15.960
and had a stash
of prescription pills.

822
00:44:16.120 --> 00:44:17.200
The ketamine?

823
00:44:17.360 --> 00:44:18.840
You think it's some kind of
drug scam?

824
00:44:19.400 --> 00:44:21.320
Steph. get on
to the pharmacy manager.

825
00:44:21.400 --> 00:44:24.160
See if they've got any concerns
over drug stock levels.

826
00:44:24.239 --> 00:44:25.440
Ma'am.

827
00:44:25.960 --> 00:44:29.760
And let's invite Miss Rosa Adeyemi
in for a little chat.

828
00:44:31.400 --> 00:44:33.040
(music fades)

829
00:44:43.080 --> 00:44:46.920
So. Rosa. after a brief audit.

830
00:44:47.000 --> 00:44:49.040
the pharmacy manager
at the hospital

831
00:44:49.440 --> 00:44:51.680
expressed his concern
over the uptick

832
00:44:51.800 --> 00:44:54.080
in the prescription
of certain drugs.

833
00:44:54.600 --> 00:44:58.680
-Ketamine. fentanyl. morphine.
-(Vera) Oh...

834
00:44:59.280 --> 00:45:02.920
Someone at the hospital
has been adapting prescriptions.

835
00:45:03.160 --> 00:45:07.400
changing dosages and filling in
scripts with fake names.

836
00:45:07.520 --> 00:45:10.000
Ghost patients
created by someone else.

837
00:45:10.600 --> 00:45:12.360
They'll trace it back to you. Rosa.

838
00:45:12.880 --> 00:45:13.880
So come on.

839
00:45:14.120 --> 00:45:16.080
Tell us how you really knew
Gabi Fischer.

840
00:45:20.080 --> 00:45:22.800
Okay. I'll tell you how I think
this scam works.

841
00:45:23.040 --> 00:45:24.920
You give drugs to Gabi Fischer.

842
00:45:25.040 --> 00:45:28.400
she gives them to Lee Critchley.
and he sells them on.

843
00:45:28.600 --> 00:45:29.600
Am I right?

844
00:45:31.560 --> 00:45:33.120
(Joe) Because fraud is one thing.

845
00:45:33.960 --> 00:45:36.440
But you need to convince us
you weren't part of her murder.

846
00:45:36.520 --> 00:45:37.520
What?

847
00:45:38.480 --> 00:45:41.360
No. I only got involved to...

848
00:45:43.360 --> 00:45:44.360
(Vera) To what?

849
00:45:45.719 --> 00:45:46.840
My dad.

850
00:45:47.640 --> 00:45:51.239
-He had an accident last year.
-I'm sorry to hear that.

851
00:45:51.840 --> 00:45:55.320
He got addicted
to prescription pain meds.

852
00:45:56.000 --> 00:45:57.760
Wanted me to help him get them.

853
00:45:58.320 --> 00:45:59.560
But because I'm a pharmacist.

854
00:45:59.640 --> 00:46:01.360
he thought
I could just help myself.

855
00:46:01.719 --> 00:46:02.880
But I told him that I couldn't.

856
00:46:03.360 --> 00:46:05.400
Hmm. oh. you just let him suffer.

857
00:46:06.719 --> 00:46:09.840
No. he found himself some dealer.

858
00:46:10.440 --> 00:46:11.440
(Joe) Lee Critchley.

859
00:46:12.200 --> 00:46:13.320
(Rosa) You need to talk to him.

860
00:46:14.160 --> 00:46:16.080
I never wanted to do
anything wrong.

861
00:46:16.160 --> 00:46:17.840
-Ah. they all say that. pet.
-(papers rustling)

862
00:46:17.960 --> 00:46:19.640
But now Dad was on a hook.

863
00:46:19.719 --> 00:46:23.080
And when he couldn't afford more.
he told Lee what my job was.

864
00:46:23.280 --> 00:46:25.239
And he put you and Gabi together.

865
00:46:25.880 --> 00:46:28.400
I had nothing to do with her death.
(breathes sharply)

866
00:46:28.560 --> 00:46:30.200
You have to believe me.

867
00:46:30.800 --> 00:46:32.160
(telephone ringing in distance)

868
00:46:34.719 --> 00:46:37.520
Well. that fraud charge'll stick.
but she's right.

869
00:46:37.600 --> 00:46:39.280
We need to find Lee Critchley.

870
00:46:39.440 --> 00:46:41.400
-You think he's done a runner?
-Er. ma'am?

871
00:46:41.480 --> 00:46:42.600
I thought you'd want to know.

872
00:46:42.680 --> 00:46:45.480
Fiona Rushden's back in the UK.
I've got an address for her.

873
00:46:45.640 --> 00:46:46.840
-(dramatic music playing)
-Right.

874
00:46:47.000 --> 00:46:48.880
-Last Rushden I talked to.
-Aye.

875
00:46:49.040 --> 00:46:50.520
Put out a wider search
for Lee Critchley.

876
00:46:50.600 --> 00:46:52.320
and let us know as soon
as you've got something.

877
00:46:52.400 --> 00:46:54.080
-(Mark) Sir.
-(seagulls squawking)

878
00:46:56.560 --> 00:46:58.480
(Fiona)
I've not spoken to Gabi in months.

879
00:46:58.800 --> 00:47:01.280
-Why? Were you avoiding her?
-(scoffs) No.

880
00:47:01.400 --> 00:47:02.800
I had no issues with her.

881
00:47:03.960 --> 00:47:04.960
(Vera) Oh. really?

882
00:47:05.040 --> 00:47:07.480
Not even when she moved in
with your mam?

883
00:47:07.840 --> 00:47:09.320
Into your old room?

884
00:47:09.440 --> 00:47:10.520
It was between the two of them.

885
00:47:11.120 --> 00:47:12.320
See. some daughters

886
00:47:12.400 --> 00:47:16.800
would've questioned the time
and money spent. Resented it. even.

887
00:47:17.680 --> 00:47:21.400
Mam has pretty firm views on us
kids striving for ourselves.

888
00:47:22.360 --> 00:47:23.800
And I'm doing all right.
(chuckles softly)

889
00:47:23.960 --> 00:47:25.880
Oh. I can see that. pet. (chuckles)

890
00:47:26.560 --> 00:47:29.040
What about Gabi splitting up
your parents' marriage?

891
00:47:29.440 --> 00:47:33.440
(chuckles) Who said she did that?
Jonathon? Dad?

892
00:47:34.880 --> 00:47:37.440
They were struggling long before
Gabi arrived.

893
00:47:41.080 --> 00:47:42.239
Look.

894
00:47:42.600 --> 00:47:45.760
What she did was terrible.
deceiving everyone.

895
00:47:45.920 --> 00:47:49.960
But it makes sense. I suppose.
As a way to keep mam's attention.

896
00:47:51.000 --> 00:47:53.400
Have you been to see your mam
since you flew back?

897
00:47:54.160 --> 00:47:55.719
-No. Why?
-(Vera) Why?

898
00:47:55.880 --> 00:47:57.600
Because of what
she's been going through.

899
00:47:58.000 --> 00:47:59.560
Grieving this lass

900
00:47:59.680 --> 00:48:01.800
and then discovering
she's been conned? (chuckles)

901
00:48:03.040 --> 00:48:05.120
You're right. I should go see her.

902
00:48:06.800 --> 00:48:08.760
Now. we're sorry
we dragged you back. pet.

903
00:48:08.840 --> 00:48:10.320
From Spain. was it?

904
00:48:11.040 --> 00:48:12.080
Yes.

905
00:48:12.200 --> 00:48:14.360
(Joe) You've been abroad
quite a few times this last year.

906
00:48:15.080 --> 00:48:17.120
Yeah. Work. mostly.

907
00:48:17.480 --> 00:48:19.360
And you're with that. er.
big law firm.

908
00:48:19.640 --> 00:48:21.400
William and Beck. right?

909
00:48:21.480 --> 00:48:24.320
I did an internship there.
but I'm starting as a trainee now.

910
00:48:24.680 --> 00:48:27.480
-Oh. congratulations.
-(chuckles)

911
00:48:32.400 --> 00:48:33.920
(Joe)
She's definitely hiding something.

912
00:48:34.000 --> 00:48:35.520
Of course. she is.

913
00:48:36.440 --> 00:48:40.239
I mean. where's she getting money
from if it's not from her mam. hmm?

914
00:48:40.600 --> 00:48:42.520
Those clothes in that flat
aren't cheap.

915
00:48:42.600 --> 00:48:44.719
and her only out of uni last year.

916
00:48:44.960 --> 00:48:46.719
I'll get Steph to look
into her finances.

917
00:48:46.800 --> 00:48:49.000
-The trip's abroad.
-(mobile phone buzzing)

918
00:48:49.200 --> 00:48:50.800
-(tense music playing)
-Mark. what's up?

919
00:48:50.880 --> 00:48:52.960
(Mark) Er. Joe. Helen Rushden's
reported an intruder.

920
00:48:53.080 --> 00:48:55.320
-You what? When?
-(Mark) Now.

921
00:48:55.920 --> 00:48:57.160
All right. we'll meet you there.

922
00:48:58.920 --> 00:49:01.560
Helen Rushden's just reported
an intruder in her house.

923
00:49:03.200 --> 00:49:05.360
Are you receiving? Please. respond.

924
00:49:05.440 --> 00:49:06.760
He could be stealing anything.

925
00:49:06.840 --> 00:49:08.480
-Look. it's under control.
-Right.

926
00:49:08.840 --> 00:49:10.400
-Mrs Rushden?
-(Steph) Do you copy?

927
00:49:10.520 --> 00:49:12.160
-Please. respond.
-(Helen) You've gotta let me in.

928
00:49:12.239 --> 00:49:14.120
-(indistinct chatter over radio)
-(Vera) What's happened?

929
00:49:14.200 --> 00:49:16.320
Well. I... There's a broken pane
in the door.

930
00:49:16.440 --> 00:49:18.040
and someone going up the stairs.

931
00:49:18.840 --> 00:49:20.120
Intruder's still inside.

932
00:49:20.200 --> 00:49:22.120
-He's trapped in a bedroom.
-Is he armed?

933
00:49:22.239 --> 00:49:24.480
Don't think so. Mark's in there
trying to talk him out.

934
00:49:24.840 --> 00:49:25.840
He's what?

935
00:49:27.719 --> 00:49:30.760
Vera! You can't go in there.

936
00:49:30.920 --> 00:49:32.880
Well. you're not actually
in charge here. Joe.

937
00:49:32.960 --> 00:49:34.560
as much as you'd like
to think you are.

938
00:49:34.760 --> 00:49:37.120
-It's not safe to do so.
-Back garden!

939
00:49:37.280 --> 00:49:38.640
(pants) We've no officers there.

940
00:49:49.960 --> 00:49:51.000
-(grunts)
-(footsteps running)

941
00:49:51.080 --> 00:49:52.080
(trouser ripping)

942
00:49:52.200 --> 00:49:54.840
-(grunts)
-Better come down now. Lee.

943
00:49:54.920 --> 00:49:57.960
-I can't! I'm stuck!
-Lee Critchley. ma'am.

944
00:49:58.160 --> 00:50:01.719
-Oh. give me strength.
-(Lee) Me trousers are caught!

945
00:50:02.239 --> 00:50:04.280
So. which one of you wants
to arrest him

946
00:50:04.360 --> 00:50:05.760
when he's at ground level?

947
00:50:05.920 --> 00:50:08.320
-Help! Get me down!
-(trouser ripping)

948
00:50:08.560 --> 00:50:10.840
-(snickers)
-(Lee's trouser ripping)

949
00:50:11.160 --> 00:50:15.440
Well. breaking into that house
wasn't very smart. was it. Lee?

950
00:50:15.520 --> 00:50:17.600
-Not to mention getting stuck.
-Hmm.

951
00:50:17.719 --> 00:50:20.840
Were you worried about what Gabi
might have left behind?

952
00:50:21.120 --> 00:50:22.680
Don't know
what you're talking about.

953
00:50:23.080 --> 00:50:25.600
Oh. an opportunistic break-in.
was it?

954
00:50:26.160 --> 00:50:28.800
Cos it seems more likely
that you were watching the house.

955
00:50:29.160 --> 00:50:32.000
waiting for her to go out.
and you thought you had time.

956
00:50:32.080 --> 00:50:34.360
Hmm. This what you were after?

957
00:50:35.239 --> 00:50:39.840
Or maybe you were worried
about these.

958
00:50:43.080 --> 00:50:45.520
And we know
you were in regular contact

959
00:50:46.120 --> 00:50:47.480
with Gabi Fisher.

960
00:50:49.280 --> 00:50:52.239
-Who?
-(Vera) Oh. Gabi McSwain.

961
00:50:53.000 --> 00:50:54.600
Ah. come on. Lee.

962
00:50:54.680 --> 00:50:56.800
We know she'd been kipping
in your spare room.

963
00:50:56.920 --> 00:51:00.480
And we know about the scam
between you and Gabi

964
00:51:00.560 --> 00:51:01.920
and that pharmacist.

965
00:51:02.160 --> 00:51:04.080
You didn't even have a burner phone
to hide your tracks.

966
00:51:04.200 --> 00:51:05.920
It's a bit of a schoolboy error.

967
00:51:06.000 --> 00:51:10.680
Plus. we have you both on CCTV
at the train station

968
00:51:10.760 --> 00:51:12.719
on the day she died.

969
00:51:13.200 --> 00:51:15.160
So. did you follow her. Lee?

970
00:51:16.239 --> 00:51:18.120
-Did you hurt her?
-No.

971
00:51:18.520 --> 00:51:21.160
-(Joe) What were you arguing about?
-About her wanting to stop.

972
00:51:21.280 --> 00:51:22.360
Stop what?

973
00:51:23.600 --> 00:51:26.640
She didn't need all that anymore.
cos she was conning that woman.

974
00:51:26.920 --> 00:51:29.400
Oh. so you knew
she was conning her?

975
00:51:29.880 --> 00:51:30.880
(Lee) Yes.

976
00:51:32.040 --> 00:51:33.760
But deep down.
it wasn't about scamming money.

977
00:51:33.880 --> 00:51:36.480
-(scoffs)
-(Lee) Look. Gabi had this gap.

978
00:51:37.280 --> 00:51:39.280
She wanted to be looked after.
Be adored.

979
00:51:40.160 --> 00:51:41.400
You know about her sister?

980
00:51:42.480 --> 00:51:43.520
Aye.

981
00:51:46.000 --> 00:51:49.280
So. when Gabi left home.
she came looking for you. did she?

982
00:51:49.719 --> 00:51:51.400
When she needed to pay her way.
is that it?

983
00:51:51.920 --> 00:51:53.440
You think I pushed her
into all of this?

984
00:51:54.000 --> 00:51:56.800
Listen. I was fine.
She's the one that needed cash.

985
00:51:57.239 --> 00:51:58.880
Started suggesting things
like signing up

986
00:51:58.960 --> 00:52:00.320
for different doctor surgeries.

987
00:52:00.400 --> 00:52:02.400
Oh. so you just helped her.
did you?

988
00:52:02.480 --> 00:52:04.320
Well. that's very noble.

989
00:52:04.880 --> 00:52:07.160
Not so noble with Rosa. though.
were you?

990
00:52:07.320 --> 00:52:08.920
Keeping her dad on a hook.

991
00:52:09.520 --> 00:52:11.680
Did Rosa know
Gabi was faking cancer?

992
00:52:11.960 --> 00:52:15.360
No. Gabi found it funny.
Rosa bought it.

993
00:52:15.440 --> 00:52:17.000
I think it gave her the idea

994
00:52:17.080 --> 00:52:18.400
to pull the same trick
on that woman.

995
00:52:18.840 --> 00:52:21.000
So. you lost her to Helen Rushden?

996
00:52:21.400 --> 00:52:23.200
First. she wants to ditch me
after everything.

997
00:52:23.400 --> 00:52:25.520
Then she's accusing me
of ruining things with the family.

998
00:52:25.640 --> 00:52:27.880
-What's that supposed to mean?
-She said I told 'em something.

999
00:52:28.280 --> 00:52:29.640
-And had you?
-No.

1000
00:52:29.719 --> 00:52:31.880
I thought what she was doing
was stupid. but I never told.

1001
00:52:32.920 --> 00:52:34.640
So. who was it who blabbed?

1002
00:52:35.600 --> 00:52:36.719
(Joe) Come on. Lee.

1003
00:52:36.800 --> 00:52:37.840
Someone killed Gabi

1004
00:52:37.960 --> 00:52:39.880
and you're saying
you had nothing to do with it.

1005
00:52:40.080 --> 00:52:41.440
Of course. I didn't. But I don't...

1006
00:52:42.280 --> 00:52:43.760
You don't what?

1007
00:52:45.760 --> 00:52:49.840
(sighs) She hated the daughter.
I know that.

1008
00:52:50.880 --> 00:52:52.080
She had a big fight with her.

1009
00:52:53.640 --> 00:52:54.760
With Fiona?

1010
00:52:57.560 --> 00:52:58.640
(telephone ringing)

1011
00:52:58.880 --> 00:53:00.719
We should hold him
and check his movements

1012
00:53:00.800 --> 00:53:02.040
after Gabi left Newcastle.

1013
00:53:02.160 --> 00:53:05.120
Yeah. right now.
I'm more interested in Fiona.

1014
00:53:06.160 --> 00:53:09.280
She told us she's had no contact
with Gabi for months.

1015
00:53:10.800 --> 00:53:13.480
Steph. did you check
Fiona Rushden's alibi?

1016
00:53:14.680 --> 00:53:17.280
-I've been on her finances.
-Well. check it.

1017
00:53:18.960 --> 00:53:21.000
Right. well.
there was definitely recent contact

1018
00:53:21.080 --> 00:53:24.120
-between her and Gabi.
-What sort of contact?

1019
00:53:24.280 --> 00:53:26.320
An email to Fiona
from one of the accounts

1020
00:53:26.400 --> 00:53:28.280
-Gabi set up.
-What?

1021
00:53:28.719 --> 00:53:32.880
Well. as a message. it's weird.
Just an attachment.

1022
00:53:33.800 --> 00:53:34.920
(Joe) Did Gabi take that?

1023
00:53:35.360 --> 00:53:37.080
(Steph) Looks like
it's been cropped from somewhere.

1024
00:53:37.360 --> 00:53:38.480
Social media?

1025
00:53:38.840 --> 00:53:41.080
Fiona's got several feeds.
but I haven't found a match yet.

1026
00:53:41.160 --> 00:53:43.640
-Well. why would she send that?
-Exactly.

1027
00:53:43.800 --> 00:53:46.000
Looks like it's supposed to be
a message in itself.

1028
00:53:46.640 --> 00:53:48.400
-So. tell us about her finances.
-(telephone ringing)

1029
00:53:48.719 --> 00:53:51.920
Well. Fiona didn't pay for those
overseas trips on her own.

1030
00:53:52.760 --> 00:53:54.239
See these payments in her account?

1031
00:53:54.560 --> 00:53:57.239
Well. they coincide with the trips.
but there's more than enough

1032
00:53:57.320 --> 00:53:58.800
to cover travel and accommodation.

1033
00:53:59.440 --> 00:54:01.080
Who's been making these payments?

1034
00:54:01.160 --> 00:54:02.719
I'm still tracing the account.
ma'am.

1035
00:54:03.160 --> 00:54:04.920
Er. ma'am. it's the morgue.

1036
00:54:05.200 --> 00:54:07.400
Er. Deborah and Matthew McSwain
have just turned up.

1037
00:54:07.560 --> 00:54:08.960
They want to view the body.

1038
00:54:11.239 --> 00:54:13.560
(melancholic music playing)

1039
00:54:17.280 --> 00:54:19.520
(cries)

1040
00:54:41.400 --> 00:54:42.400
Thank you.

1041
00:54:43.800 --> 00:54:45.200
-For allowing us.
-(clicks tongue)

1042
00:54:45.800 --> 00:54:49.239
It's good for us to get
a formal identification at last.

1043
00:54:49.920 --> 00:54:52.680
-If we hadn't let her go. maybe...
-Hey. hey. no.

1044
00:54:53.520 --> 00:54:54.680
Look. I'm sorry. love.

1045
00:54:54.760 --> 00:54:58.320
You told us that Gabi
had been involved in petty crime.

1046
00:54:59.239 --> 00:55:01.440
After her sister got sick. yeah.

1047
00:55:01.640 --> 00:55:03.480
No. it's just that
she has been involved

1048
00:55:03.600 --> 00:55:06.360
in illegally obtaining
and distributing drugs.

1049
00:55:07.160 --> 00:55:08.440
-Drugs?
-No.

1050
00:55:09.719 --> 00:55:11.320
No. there wasn't...
There was nothing like that.

1051
00:55:12.880 --> 00:55:16.200
(hesitates) Look. I...
I'm sorry. could you excuse us?

1052
00:55:22.040 --> 00:55:23.080
(traffic whizzing)

1053
00:55:23.160 --> 00:55:25.760
(Vera) Imagine having to bury
a second daughter.

1054
00:55:28.200 --> 00:55:30.000
Blaming themselves for it. too.

1055
00:55:30.080 --> 00:55:31.760
Did you ask them
why they didn't search for her?

1056
00:55:31.840 --> 00:55:33.200
(Vera) Well.
they'd already told us.

1057
00:55:33.280 --> 00:55:34.360
hadn't they?

1058
00:55:34.480 --> 00:55:37.360
She was trouble.
They were glad when she left.

1059
00:55:39.400 --> 00:55:40.719
(Mark) So. I've got this mate.

1060
00:55:40.960 --> 00:55:42.800
He's. er. a local copper
up in Berwick.

1061
00:55:43.040 --> 00:55:44.560
Thought it was worth
giving him a call.

1062
00:55:45.160 --> 00:55:46.640
Had quite a story as well.

1063
00:55:48.280 --> 00:55:49.320
Well. let's hear it.

1064
00:55:49.520 --> 00:55:51.840
Yeah. so Gabi's mam
used to help out

1065
00:55:51.920 --> 00:55:53.400
with the daughter of a friend.

1066
00:55:53.480 --> 00:55:55.440
Pick her up from school.
give her tea some nights.

1067
00:55:55.520 --> 00:55:56.840
that sort of thing.
(breathes sharply)

1068
00:55:56.960 --> 00:56:00.239
Anyway. erm. anonymous call
come into the police saying

1069
00:56:00.320 --> 00:56:01.920
that Deborah was hurting the child.

1070
00:56:02.000 --> 00:56:03.400
(Vera) Yeah. but we checked.

1071
00:56:03.480 --> 00:56:05.239
There was no record of her
being charged.

1072
00:56:05.600 --> 00:56:06.600
(Mark) Er. no. ma'am.

1073
00:56:06.680 --> 00:56:08.880
Er. police had to look into it.
obviously.

1074
00:56:08.960 --> 00:56:12.280
-So. the case was dismissed?
-(Mark) Yeah. no evidence at all.

1075
00:56:12.360 --> 00:56:13.880
(breathes sharply)
The girl had been playing

1076
00:56:13.960 --> 00:56:16.840
in the playground and fell
just before the tip-off come in.

1077
00:56:16.920 --> 00:56:19.719
Er. she gashed her arm.
It was a total accident.

1078
00:56:19.840 --> 00:56:21.320
Plenty of witnesses around.

1079
00:56:21.400 --> 00:56:24.920
So. hang on. are you saying
this anonymous caller was Gabi?

1080
00:56:25.000 --> 00:56:28.120
Well. it was never confirmed
and she disappeared straight after.

1081
00:56:28.239 --> 00:56:29.880
but her parents thought so.

1082
00:56:29.960 --> 00:56:32.520
Maliciously accused her own mother
and then scarpered.

1083
00:56:33.160 --> 00:56:35.000
No wonder they didn't go
looking for her.

1084
00:56:35.080 --> 00:56:36.200
(Steph) Okay. thanks.

1085
00:56:37.280 --> 00:56:40.640
The payments into Fiona's account
came from a "Jonah Green."

1086
00:56:41.000 --> 00:56:42.600
And who's Jonah Green?

1087
00:56:43.040 --> 00:56:45.239
A senior partner
at William and Beck.

1088
00:56:45.560 --> 00:56:47.520
What. the firm Fiona works for?

1089
00:56:48.640 --> 00:56:50.600
(dramatic music playing)

1090
00:56:55.400 --> 00:56:57.640
-(Joe yawns)
-The pace too slow for you.

1091
00:56:57.719 --> 00:56:59.280
now you're back in Newcastle?

1092
00:56:59.360 --> 00:57:01.280
(Joe) Oh. I was up late
sorting stuff out.

1093
00:57:01.440 --> 00:57:03.280
-What. unpacking crockery?
-(rain pattering)

1094
00:57:03.400 --> 00:57:06.000
-Connecting the Wi-Fi?
-No.

1095
00:57:06.600 --> 00:57:08.840
Although you wouldn't be joking
if you'd just uprooted teenagers

1096
00:57:08.920 --> 00:57:11.040
to a new city
and hadn't sorted the Wi-Fi.

1097
00:57:12.360 --> 00:57:14.200
Oh. (smack lips)

1098
00:57:15.440 --> 00:57:16.480
This your dad?

1099
00:57:17.920 --> 00:57:19.000
Aye.

1100
00:57:20.160 --> 00:57:21.560
We should really move him
to our hospice.

1101
00:57:21.640 --> 00:57:24.720
-but it just feels...
-Excuse me. Sorry to keep you.

1102
00:57:24.800 --> 00:57:26.480
Mr Green has made himself
available.

1103
00:57:26.800 --> 00:57:29.680
Oh. has he?
That's very nice of him.

1104
00:57:34.360 --> 00:57:36.320
She's had a charm bypass.

1105
00:57:37.200 --> 00:57:39.440
I helped Fiona get her internship.

1106
00:57:40.200 --> 00:57:42.640
-I'm pleased she's now a trainee.
-(Vera) Hmm.

1107
00:57:43.000 --> 00:57:45.600
So. why have you been giving her
money. love?

1108
00:57:45.720 --> 00:57:48.320
(chuckles nervously. hesitates)
That's private?

1109
00:57:48.600 --> 00:57:50.600
(Vera) Oh. I wouldn't go poking
into private matters

1110
00:57:50.760 --> 00:57:54.400
if I didn't have to.
but this is a murder investigation.

1111
00:57:54.960 --> 00:57:56.320
And I don't see the connection.

1112
00:57:56.480 --> 00:57:59.280
Because she was coy
about her trips abroad.

1113
00:57:59.360 --> 00:58:02.440
and now you're hiding
why you were sending her money.

1114
00:58:02.560 --> 00:58:04.160
which makes me curious.

1115
00:58:04.320 --> 00:58:07.760
Sounds like gossipy nosiness.
not serious evidence gathering.

1116
00:58:07.840 --> 00:58:10.680
Sounds like you'd rather come down
to the station to talk.

1117
00:58:11.200 --> 00:58:12.320
(dramatic music playing)

1118
00:58:12.400 --> 00:58:14.200
Ah. come on. there's no need
for that. is there?

1119
00:58:14.920 --> 00:58:16.720
We can deal with this
nice and easy.

1120
00:58:17.480 --> 00:58:18.840
Maybe at Mr Green's home.

1121
00:58:19.640 --> 00:58:22.160
(Jonah chuckles. hesitates)
All right. Look...

1122
00:58:23.240 --> 00:58:25.760
there's an arrangement
between Fiona and I. okay?

1123
00:58:26.000 --> 00:58:28.480
-All above board.
-"An arrangement"?

1124
00:58:30.720 --> 00:58:33.760
(hesitates) Made via a website.

1125
00:58:34.520 --> 00:58:36.840
This is like getting blood
from a stone.

1126
00:58:36.960 --> 00:58:39.000
Show us the website and we're gone.

1127
00:58:39.200 --> 00:58:40.600
(sighs)

1128
00:58:42.840 --> 00:58:44.800
(keyboard clacking)

1129
00:58:45.800 --> 00:58:48.720
-What is this?
-(Joe) It's a sugaring site.

1130
00:58:49.520 --> 00:58:51.480
It's where young women
can advertise themselves

1131
00:58:51.560 --> 00:58:54.720
to spend time with richer.
usually older men.

1132
00:58:55.040 --> 00:58:56.480
(keyboard clacking)

1133
00:58:58.880 --> 00:59:00.560
I see.

1134
00:59:03.040 --> 00:59:05.560
And that's the photo Gabi sent.

1135
00:59:06.760 --> 00:59:09.760
If she cropped it from that site.
she knew Fiona was sugaring.

1136
00:59:09.880 --> 00:59:12.680
Aye. and I wonder
how Fiona felt about that.

1137
00:59:12.800 --> 00:59:15.120
I want her brought in
for questioning today.

1138
00:59:15.240 --> 00:59:16.640
-(police siren wailing)
-(music concludes)

1139
00:59:16.720 --> 00:59:19.400
(chuckles nervously)
Men want one thing.

1140
00:59:20.280 --> 00:59:23.320
This is quid pro quo.
To get what I want.

1141
00:59:23.880 --> 00:59:25.440
(Vera) Oh. aye?
And what's that. love?

1142
00:59:25.520 --> 00:59:28.440
Some professional advice.
Some money to offset my debts.

1143
00:59:28.600 --> 00:59:31.600
-Hmm. Plus. a few luxury trips.
-(chuckles)

1144
00:59:32.920 --> 00:59:34.520
Everything's agreed.

1145
00:59:34.640 --> 00:59:38.640
Everyone is willing.
There's no "Me too" here.

1146
00:59:39.400 --> 00:59:42.680
-(Vera) No. I'm not judging. love.
-Really?

1147
00:59:42.760 --> 00:59:44.160
But I'm guessing

1148
00:59:44.840 --> 00:59:47.280
none of your colleagues
know about this...

1149
00:59:48.480 --> 00:59:49.520
or your mam?

1150
00:59:50.520 --> 00:59:52.240
I saw what happened
when my brother asked for money.

1151
00:59:52.560 --> 00:59:53.600
(Joe) Jonathon?

1152
00:59:54.360 --> 00:59:56.080
-What happened?
-(chuckles)

1153
00:59:56.800 --> 00:59:58.320
He crashed and burned.

1154
00:59:59.040 --> 01:00:02.240
(Vera)
So. if your mam's money tap is off.

1155
01:00:02.480 --> 01:00:04.720
well. it must have been hard
seeing her give Gabi

1156
01:00:04.800 --> 01:00:07.760
-everything she wanted.
-I said I didn't care about Gabi.

1157
01:00:08.320 --> 01:00:10.600
(Joe) You also said you hadn't had
any contact at all.

1158
01:00:11.200 --> 01:00:15.440
But that's not true. is it?
Because Gabi sent you that photo.

1159
01:00:18.320 --> 01:00:20.160
Cos she found out
about your "sugaring".

1160
01:00:20.240 --> 01:00:21.320
(pensive music playing)

1161
01:00:21.400 --> 01:00:23.200
I'd considered going back home.
okay?

1162
01:00:23.480 --> 01:00:26.480
About a month or so back.
But Gabi was well settled.

1163
01:00:26.640 --> 01:00:27.720
Didn't want me ruining it.

1164
01:00:28.000 --> 01:00:29.800
So. what was the picture? A threat?

1165
01:00:30.640 --> 01:00:31.920
"Stay away or I tell."

1166
01:00:33.160 --> 01:00:34.520
She wanted Mam all to herself.

1167
01:00:34.840 --> 01:00:36.280
Well. that must have been terrible.

1168
01:00:36.360 --> 01:00:39.320
(laughs) God. do you want to hear
I hated her?

1169
01:00:39.480 --> 01:00:40.520
Well. didn't you?

1170
01:00:41.360 --> 01:00:44.480
Even if I did.
it doesn't mean I'd hurt her.

1171
01:00:45.760 --> 01:00:48.520
And that's what you're supposed
to be finding out. right?

1172
01:00:51.640 --> 01:00:52.760
(Vera) Steph...

1173
01:00:52.840 --> 01:00:55.040
How are you doing
with Fiona's alibi?

1174
01:00:55.120 --> 01:00:56.120
Checks out. ma'am.

1175
01:00:56.200 --> 01:00:57.640
She was at work.
Plenty of witnesses.

1176
01:00:57.720 --> 01:00:59.040
-Flew to Spain that evening.
-(sighs)

1177
01:00:59.160 --> 01:01:01.640
Oh. and by the way.
we can also place her dad.

1178
01:01:01.840 --> 01:01:02.840
Tom?

1179
01:01:02.920 --> 01:01:04.880
(Steph) Mark spoke to a mechanic
in his garage.

1180
01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:07.600
They can vouch for him till five.
but they also suggested

1181
01:01:07.680 --> 01:01:09.600
he'd more than likely go
to The Griffin for a few.

1182
01:01:09.680 --> 01:01:10.880
-before heading off.
-Aye.

1183
01:01:10.960 --> 01:01:12.600
So. he went to the pub
and then the garage?

1184
01:01:12.720 --> 01:01:15.240
Yep. Eyewitnesses and CCTV.

1185
01:01:15.320 --> 01:01:18.720
(Vera) Okay. Steph. carry on
with the family's finances.

1186
01:01:19.040 --> 01:01:22.560
(smack lips) Now. Fiona said
her brother asked Helen for money.

1187
01:01:23.560 --> 01:01:25.760
I wonder what he wanted that for?

1188
01:01:26.520 --> 01:01:28.280
-(mobile phone buzzing)
-Speak of the devil.

1189
01:01:29.440 --> 01:01:30.480
DI Ashworth.

1190
01:01:32.920 --> 01:01:34.560
Sorry. you're with your mother
and who turned up?

1191
01:01:35.600 --> 01:01:36.640
Mam has asked you to go.

1192
01:01:36.720 --> 01:01:39.360
-I didn't mean... I just wanted...
-You need to leave.

1193
01:01:39.480 --> 01:01:40.880
-(sighs) It's just...
-(Jonathon) Now.

1194
01:01:40.960 --> 01:01:43.680
...she used to live here.
my girl. with her.

1195
01:01:43.800 --> 01:01:45.720
Yeah. And I wish she hadn't.

1196
01:01:46.640 --> 01:01:48.320
I wish I'd never met your daughter.

1197
01:01:48.440 --> 01:01:50.200
-You wanna know what it was like...
-(door knocking)

1198
01:01:50.280 --> 01:01:52.280
...looking after her?
I can't tell you.

1199
01:01:52.400 --> 01:01:53.840
Cos it was all lies!

1200
01:01:54.400 --> 01:01:55.760
Your daughter was nothing

1201
01:01:55.840 --> 01:01:58.320
-but a manipulative. deceitful...
-Oh. let's leave it right there.

1202
01:01:58.440 --> 01:02:00.080
You produced nothing.
but a monster!

1203
01:02:00.200 --> 01:02:02.520
-Get her out of my house!
-Come on. pet. it's time to go.

1204
01:02:02.600 --> 01:02:03.640
Come on.

1205
01:02:05.800 --> 01:02:07.600
(Deborah) I just...
I just need a minute.

1206
01:02:07.680 --> 01:02:09.360
-(birds chirping)
-(dog barking)

1207
01:02:11.440 --> 01:02:13.400
Get her a cup of tea. A sweet one.

1208
01:02:15.040 --> 01:02:16.200
All right. I'll go.

1209
01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:19.280
-Can you give us a fiver?
-I'll get it.

1210
01:02:25.200 --> 01:02:26.400
(Deborah) Matthew's coming.

1211
01:02:27.480 --> 01:02:29.800
His boat's in
for an overhaul anyway.

1212
01:02:30.160 --> 01:02:32.040
-(hawker) What do you need?
-(Joe) A cup of tea. please.

1213
01:02:32.120 --> 01:02:34.360
Did he know
you've been to see Helen?

1214
01:02:34.880 --> 01:02:35.960
(Deborah) No.

1215
01:02:37.320 --> 01:02:39.360
Didn't even wanna come
yesterday to see...

1216
01:02:40.280 --> 01:02:42.280
(sighs) ...Gabi.

1217
01:02:46.800 --> 01:02:48.040
He'll be appalled.

1218
01:02:49.280 --> 01:02:50.840
Why did you go. love?

1219
01:02:52.600 --> 01:02:54.800
That woman was doing something
I should have been.

1220
01:02:56.520 --> 01:02:57.600
Looking after her.

1221
01:03:01.360 --> 01:03:02.360
Was she right...

1222
01:03:04.160 --> 01:03:07.960
-about me raising a monster?
-Oh. listen. love.

1223
01:03:08.600 --> 01:03:11.120
Your mam and dad always mess you up

1224
01:03:11.200 --> 01:03:12.640
one way or another.

1225
01:03:13.600 --> 01:03:15.080
But kids become adults

1226
01:03:15.160 --> 01:03:17.120
and take responsibility
for their actions.

1227
01:03:17.200 --> 01:03:20.040
You're not to blame
for what Gabi did. You're not.

1228
01:03:20.360 --> 01:03:21.800
(sombre music playing)

1229
01:03:22.440 --> 01:03:24.960
-Cup of tea for you.
-Thanks.

1230
01:03:27.600 --> 01:03:28.920
(sighs) He's here.

1231
01:03:29.440 --> 01:03:30.720
(engine rumbling)

1232
01:03:36.320 --> 01:03:39.080
You all right? Come here.

1233
01:03:41.720 --> 01:03:42.760
All right.

1234
01:03:44.560 --> 01:03:45.920
(car door opening)

1235
01:03:48.400 --> 01:03:49.800
I'm sorry.

1236
01:03:51.200 --> 01:03:52.240
Okay.

1237
01:03:55.240 --> 01:03:57.520
Mr McSwain.
can I have a quick word?

1238
01:04:02.760 --> 01:04:05.080
Now. just before Gabi left home.

1239
01:04:05.160 --> 01:04:09.360
there was an accusation of abuse
levelled at your wife.

1240
01:04:10.600 --> 01:04:13.960
-She was exonerated. Completely.
-We know.

1241
01:04:14.520 --> 01:04:16.360
But was that the reason
you never looked for Gabi?

1242
01:04:18.760 --> 01:04:20.160
Even being accused...

1243
01:04:21.680 --> 01:04:22.920
investigated...

1244
01:04:24.280 --> 01:04:28.560
people heard. hmm.
started looking at her differently.

1245
01:04:29.440 --> 01:04:30.520
Still do.

1246
01:04:32.080 --> 01:04:33.680
And the shame that that brought.

1247
01:04:36.040 --> 01:04:37.240
Deb's needed time.

1248
01:04:39.000 --> 01:04:40.000
And you?

1249
01:04:40.200 --> 01:04:43.360
I. er. I hoped we could find Gabi
one day.

1250
01:04:44.600 --> 01:04:47.120
If nothing else. I wanted to try
and understand how she could...

1251
01:04:49.280 --> 01:04:50.280
Anyway. erm...

1252
01:04:51.360 --> 01:04:52.720
won't happen now. Will it?

1253
01:04:58.040 --> 01:04:59.800
-Steph?
-(Steph) Helen's company.

1254
01:04:59.880 --> 01:05:02.280
So. I've looked at the accounts
and Jonathon Rushden's

1255
01:05:02.360 --> 01:05:03.640
been managing
the company recently.

1256
01:05:04.120 --> 01:05:05.560
But I think
he's been mismanaging it.

1257
01:05:05.640 --> 01:05:06.880
(Joe) What do you mean?

1258
01:05:06.960 --> 01:05:08.840
Well. he's been funnelling money
from the coffee shops

1259
01:05:08.920 --> 01:05:10.280
into a business in his name.

1260
01:05:10.400 --> 01:05:12.080
Provides catering
and entertainment.

1261
01:05:12.320 --> 01:05:14.360
-But it's sinking.
-Is that the boss?

1262
01:05:14.600 --> 01:05:16.360
Yeah. Er. hold on. ma'am.
Mark wants you.

1263
01:05:16.480 --> 01:05:17.600
Right. go on. Mark.

1264
01:05:17.680 --> 01:05:20.280
(Mark) Ma'am.
Freya Rushden's left a message

1265
01:05:20.360 --> 01:05:22.520
-withdrawing her statement.
-Ah. you're kidding?

1266
01:05:22.600 --> 01:05:25.840
She's now denying Jonathon was home
all day last Wednesday.

1267
01:05:26.360 --> 01:05:28.960
Now. why would a wife go
and do that?

1268
01:05:30.160 --> 01:05:31.160
Hmm?

1269
01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:33.120
(Joe) Go on. Mark.

1270
01:05:35.160 --> 01:05:36.400
(Vera) Now. come on.

1271
01:05:36.920 --> 01:05:38.440
What's this all about. love?

1272
01:05:39.760 --> 01:05:41.920
You see.
by withdrawing your statement.

1273
01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:44.360
what you're really saying is
that you lied to us

1274
01:05:44.480 --> 01:05:45.520
the first time round.

1275
01:05:46.040 --> 01:05:48.600
-I'm sorry about that.
-Hmm?

1276
01:05:49.600 --> 01:05:51.680
-So. why do it?
-(Jack) Mammy!

1277
01:05:52.520 --> 01:05:53.680
-It broke again.
-Hang on.

1278
01:05:53.800 --> 01:05:56.000
So. what are you now saying
happened last Wednesday?

1279
01:05:56.920 --> 01:06:00.160
Jonathon worked from home.
then he went out. A bit after four.

1280
01:06:00.320 --> 01:06:02.720
-How long was he out for?
-(Freya) Two or three hours.

1281
01:06:02.880 --> 01:06:05.000
Er. he wasn't back
till after Jack's bedtime.

1282
01:06:05.200 --> 01:06:06.800
-(Jack) Mammy!
-Look. I have to...

1283
01:06:06.880 --> 01:06:09.280
-Where did he go?
-Ask him.

1284
01:06:09.560 --> 01:06:13.120
So. he was doing something.
but you don't wanna tell us what?

1285
01:06:13.280 --> 01:06:15.320
Why should I tell you
his dirty secrets?

1286
01:06:15.600 --> 01:06:16.600
He can tell you himself.

1287
01:06:17.720 --> 01:06:20.760
-Where is he. love?
-He's in The Griffin with his dad.

1288
01:06:21.280 --> 01:06:23.480
-I'm done.
-Come on. Let's go to the pub.

1289
01:06:24.960 --> 01:06:26.840
-(Tom yelling) Why? How could you?
-(grunts)

1290
01:06:27.120 --> 01:06:28.320
-(grunts)
-Hey. hey. hey. hey!

1291
01:06:28.440 --> 01:06:30.320
-What's this all about?
-(Joe) Calm. calm. calm.

1292
01:06:30.440 --> 01:06:32.960
(Jonathon) He said come by.
then started laying into us.

1293
01:06:33.120 --> 01:06:35.680
-Because I know the truth!
-(overlapping chatter)

1294
01:06:35.960 --> 01:06:37.000
What truth?

1295
01:06:37.160 --> 01:06:41.480
He knew Gabi was a fraud all along!
And he didn't tell us!

1296
01:06:41.960 --> 01:06:44.440
Not Helen. not me. no one!

1297
01:06:45.400 --> 01:06:46.720
He doesn't know what he's saying.
man.

1298
01:06:46.880 --> 01:06:48.560
(Tom) And you want to know
why he kept quiet?

1299
01:06:48.680 --> 01:06:49.760
You want to know why?

1300
01:06:50.480 --> 01:06:53.760
Because he was sleeping with her!
(pants)

1301
01:06:55.360 --> 01:06:57.560
He was sleeping with Gabi.

1302
01:06:59.440 --> 01:07:01.520
-(music concludes)
-(indistinct chatter)

1303
01:07:01.720 --> 01:07:02.960
Thanks. love.

1304
01:07:04.960 --> 01:07:06.000
(groans)

1305
01:07:08.360 --> 01:07:12.120
Are you really saying
he knew Gabi was faking cancer?

1306
01:07:12.360 --> 01:07:13.560
(sighs)

1307
01:07:14.640 --> 01:07:16.080
And he was sleeping with her?

1308
01:07:16.840 --> 01:07:17.880
(Tom) Yes.

1309
01:07:18.800 --> 01:07:20.040
Freya told me.

1310
01:07:21.760 --> 01:07:22.800
How'd she know?

1311
01:07:24.520 --> 01:07:25.720
She's his wife.

1312
01:07:27.640 --> 01:07:29.520
She was sorry I'd lost mine.

1313
01:07:32.840 --> 01:07:34.000
Hold that.

1314
01:07:34.800 --> 01:07:36.200
(police siren wailing)

1315
01:07:36.320 --> 01:07:38.200
-(Joe) How's he doing?
-(indistinct chatter over radio)

1316
01:07:38.280 --> 01:07:40.240
-Uniform are gonna see him home.
-(indistinct chatter)

1317
01:07:40.360 --> 01:07:42.640
-And what about this one?
-He'll live.

1318
01:07:42.960 --> 01:07:44.560
-(Jonathon) What's happening?
-Yeah. thanks. pet.

1319
01:07:44.680 --> 01:07:46.600
-(police officer) Thanks. Ma'am.
-(Jonathon) Can I go yet?

1320
01:07:46.760 --> 01:07:48.280
Ah. well. that depends.

1321
01:07:48.480 --> 01:07:50.480
And what's your version
of all this?

1322
01:07:50.800 --> 01:07:54.320
Well. you saw Dad. He's drunk.
He was lashing out.

1323
01:07:54.480 --> 01:07:58.520
Hmm. He said it was your missus
told him about you and Gabi.

1324
01:07:58.680 --> 01:08:00.600
Things have been difficult
between me and Freya.

1325
01:08:01.800 --> 01:08:03.560
-Money worries.
-Really?

1326
01:08:06.080 --> 01:08:08.240
If she's got hold
of some nonsense idea.

1327
01:08:08.800 --> 01:08:09.800
doesn't make it true.

1328
01:08:09.960 --> 01:08:11.440
So. you weren't sleeping with Gabi.
then?

1329
01:08:11.520 --> 01:08:12.760
Of course. not.

1330
01:08:12.880 --> 01:08:15.040
Just cos if you were.
I mean. you'd want it kept quiet.

1331
01:08:15.560 --> 01:08:18.840
-You'd want her to keep it quiet.
-(Jonathon) Are you serious?

1332
01:08:20.320 --> 01:08:21.640
Throwing accusations at me

1333
01:08:21.760 --> 01:08:23.720
when my Dad's the one
punching people?

1334
01:08:24.439 --> 01:08:27.080
-Why not look at him. eh?
-Because he hasn't just lost

1335
01:08:27.200 --> 01:08:29.479
his alibi for the day
Gabi died. pet.

1336
01:08:31.160 --> 01:08:34.240
But we will bear in mind
that you think your own father

1337
01:08:34.360 --> 01:08:36.720
should be considered
as a murder suspect.

1338
01:08:36.840 --> 01:08:38.680
Hmm. Shall we?

1339
01:08:42.200 --> 01:08:43.680
(Joe) I'll gather anything
we've got on her.

1340
01:08:44.120 --> 01:08:46.400
And run his car plates
from last Wednesday.

1341
01:08:46.640 --> 01:08:48.040
Cell site data. too.

1342
01:08:48.120 --> 01:08:51.160
I want him and his missus
brought in for questioning

1343
01:08:51.240 --> 01:08:52.760
first thing in the morning.

1344
01:08:52.840 --> 01:08:54.000
(seagulls squawking)

1345
01:09:02.720 --> 01:09:04.439
-(drawer closing. opening)
-(indistinct chatter)

1346
01:09:04.560 --> 01:09:05.880
Jonathon's ready.
and I've got Freya

1347
01:09:05.960 --> 01:09:07.360
-in the other interview room.
-Eh.

1348
01:09:07.439 --> 01:09:08.600
-Anything on her?
-(drawer closing)

1349
01:09:08.680 --> 01:09:11.080
No. Squeaky clean
and fully cooperative today.

1350
01:09:11.320 --> 01:09:13.240
Volunteered access to her phone
and everything.

1351
01:09:13.479 --> 01:09:15.040
-Right.
-(drawer closing)

1352
01:09:15.240 --> 01:09:17.040
Joe. have you got any painkillers?

1353
01:09:17.240 --> 01:09:19.240
Have you not booked
to see the dentist yet?

1354
01:09:19.320 --> 01:09:21.000
Well. I'm trying to solve
a murder here.

1355
01:09:21.080 --> 01:09:23.760
-in case you hadn't noticed.
-I've some in me desk.

1356
01:09:24.920 --> 01:09:27.960
Sir. any chance I could sit in
if you're interviewing Freya?

1357
01:09:28.040 --> 01:09:29.520
It's just I haven't. yet. With her.

1358
01:09:30.560 --> 01:09:32.400
-How long you been here now?
-Four months.

1359
01:09:32.479 --> 01:09:34.120
Well. then it's about time.
isn't it?

1360
01:09:34.760 --> 01:09:37.960
-Sure. get ready.
-(drawer opening)

1361
01:09:40.280 --> 01:09:41.280
What are you doing?

1362
01:09:41.360 --> 01:09:44.040
You were so busy chatting.
I thought I'd get them meself.

1363
01:09:47.560 --> 01:09:50.360
So. Jonathon says you're upset.
and confused.

1364
01:09:50.520 --> 01:09:53.000
-and you're angry about money.
-(Freya) No.

1365
01:09:53.080 --> 01:09:54.560
that's not what's happening.

1366
01:09:54.920 --> 01:09:56.840
I know his business is going badly.

1367
01:09:57.120 --> 01:09:59.360
He talked about re-mortgaging
the house. for God's sake.

1368
01:09:59.640 --> 01:10:02.920
-So. you are anxious about money?
-It's totally natural.

1369
01:10:03.320 --> 01:10:06.560
-Worried about yourself. your son?
-Fine. yeah. okay.

1370
01:10:07.000 --> 01:10:09.120
But that's nothing to do
with what I told Tom.

1371
01:10:10.280 --> 01:10:11.800
(Jonathon)
I'm sorting the finances.

1372
01:10:13.080 --> 01:10:14.160
It's not serious.

1373
01:10:15.080 --> 01:10:16.120
Freya just worries.

1374
01:10:16.200 --> 01:10:18.680
Well. it's serious enough
to siphon money away

1375
01:10:18.760 --> 01:10:20.479
from your mam's business.

1376
01:10:21.160 --> 01:10:24.200
Here. Here. Here.

1377
01:10:24.320 --> 01:10:26.400
How we run our company
is a matter for my ma and me.

1378
01:10:26.479 --> 01:10:29.840
Except I'd lay good money.
she's no idea about any of it.

1379
01:10:30.360 --> 01:10:34.280
Taking money from her shops
to feed a failing side project.

1380
01:10:34.520 --> 01:10:36.200
Not her style. love.

1381
01:10:36.360 --> 01:10:39.960
And claiming your wife's hysterical
won't wash with me. pet.

1382
01:10:40.120 --> 01:10:46.920
So. why don't we have
an honest talk about you and Gabi?

1383
01:10:48.240 --> 01:10:50.439
(Joe) How did you find out
that Jonathon was having an affair?

1384
01:10:51.560 --> 01:10:52.960
You really want the clichés?

1385
01:10:53.439 --> 01:10:57.320
Okay. so you were suspicious.
So. what do you do? You follow him?

1386
01:10:57.920 --> 01:10:58.960
Or follow Gabi?

1387
01:10:59.600 --> 01:11:01.520
Maybe it spiralled.
The two of you fought.

1388
01:11:02.240 --> 01:11:06.280
(Freya hesitates) Fought? No.
I suspected an affair.

1389
01:11:06.720 --> 01:11:08.000
But not with Gabi.

1390
01:11:08.800 --> 01:11:10.720
It wasn't until after she was...

1391
01:11:13.280 --> 01:11:16.479
-How he reacted to that.
-And how did he react?

1392
01:11:16.600 --> 01:11:18.720
(Freya) He didn't wanna talk
about it at all.

1393
01:11:19.600 --> 01:11:21.800
Till it finally made sense to me.

1394
01:11:22.680 --> 01:11:26.520
Yesterday. I confronted him.
And he denied it. of course.

1395
01:11:26.720 --> 01:11:28.680
Said I didn't know
what I was talking about.

1396
01:11:28.760 --> 01:11:30.400
Didn't know the first thing
about Gabi.

1397
01:11:31.200 --> 01:11:34.800
Blurted out about her cancer.
How he'd known that had been a lie.

1398
01:11:35.040 --> 01:11:36.600
Well. that must have come
as a shock.

1399
01:11:36.720 --> 01:11:37.960
It was a distraction.

1400
01:11:38.080 --> 01:11:40.200
Have you any proof of this affair
with Gabi?

1401
01:11:40.760 --> 01:11:43.280
You need proof? Go find it.

1402
01:11:44.479 --> 01:11:45.520
I don't.

1403
01:11:46.479 --> 01:11:47.600
I know.

1404
01:11:49.320 --> 01:11:50.560
(scoffs)

1405
01:11:51.360 --> 01:11:53.720
You seriously think I'd sleep
with the girl me mam took in?

1406
01:11:54.640 --> 01:11:56.040
After I knew Gabi was conning her?

1407
01:11:56.800 --> 01:11:57.800
(clicks tongue)

1408
01:11:57.920 --> 01:12:00.600
Yeah. sounds ridiculous
when you put it like that.

1409
01:12:00.720 --> 01:12:02.080
(papers rustling)

1410
01:12:02.439 --> 01:12:05.560
So. you won't be worried
when my forensics team

1411
01:12:05.640 --> 01:12:07.320
go through Gabi's clothes...

1412
01:12:08.320 --> 01:12:11.479
to see if there's any evidence
of a sexual relationship with you?

1413
01:12:12.680 --> 01:12:15.000
-What?
-Your clothes too. love.

1414
01:12:17.960 --> 01:12:20.439
(Joe) Where did Jonathon say
he went. the day that Gabi died?

1415
01:12:20.800 --> 01:12:23.320
He said he had to speak
to someone about a loan.

1416
01:12:23.680 --> 01:12:26.280
But from some kind of shady source.

1417
01:12:27.320 --> 01:12:29.360
So. he wanted it kept quiet
from you lot.

1418
01:12:29.560 --> 01:12:30.680
And you agreed?

1419
01:12:31.160 --> 01:12:33.120
(Joe) But now you're worried
about where he really went.

1420
01:12:33.439 --> 01:12:35.240
And if he had something to do
with Gabi's death.

1421
01:12:35.520 --> 01:12:38.280
(hesitates) I... What? No.

1422
01:12:39.479 --> 01:12:41.560
Because that's what
we're worried about.

1423
01:12:42.160 --> 01:12:44.479
You do realise
that we're investigating a murder

1424
01:12:44.560 --> 01:12:46.200
and not your husband's fidelity?

1425
01:12:50.080 --> 01:12:52.479
It's still a bit
"He said. she said". isn't it?

1426
01:12:52.560 --> 01:12:56.160
Er. ma'am. we've got him.
ANPR on Jonathon's car.

1427
01:12:56.280 --> 01:12:58.360
Plus. corroborate
and cell site data.

1428
01:12:58.640 --> 01:13:00.080
(indistinct chatter)

1429
01:13:00.520 --> 01:13:02.320
Well done. Mark.

1430
01:13:03.840 --> 01:13:06.560
Right. You care to join me.
DI Ashworth?

1431
01:13:07.600 --> 01:13:08.760
Good work in there.

1432
01:13:12.600 --> 01:13:14.439
-What's this?
-(Vera) Your car was flagged

1433
01:13:14.520 --> 01:13:19.280
on an ANPR camera in Bewton. 17:09.
last Wednesday.

1434
01:13:19.760 --> 01:13:21.920
That puts you in the area
that Gabi's body was found

1435
01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:23.040
on the day that she died.

1436
01:13:23.320 --> 01:13:27.040
(Vera) And calls and GPRS data
from your phone

1437
01:13:27.439 --> 01:13:29.000
corroborate the location.

1438
01:13:29.200 --> 01:13:31.080
So. if I were you. love.

1439
01:13:31.720 --> 01:13:34.439
I'd start talking. And fast.

1440
01:13:36.840 --> 01:13:37.960
(sighs)

1441
01:13:38.960 --> 01:13:39.960
(Vera) Okay.

1442
01:13:40.439 --> 01:13:43.560
So. when did you find out
Gabi had been faking her cancer?

1443
01:13:44.640 --> 01:13:45.760
About a month ago.

1444
01:13:46.439 --> 01:13:48.080
I just asked questions
Mam never did.

1445
01:13:48.479 --> 01:13:49.600
(Joe) Like?

1446
01:13:50.160 --> 01:13:51.920
Why did she really
worm into Mam's life?

1447
01:13:52.640 --> 01:13:54.720
Why wasn't she on social media?

1448
01:13:55.439 --> 01:13:56.840
Then I looked up her consultants.

1449
01:13:57.560 --> 01:14:00.280
-Found no record of 'em.
-Ah. quite the discovery.

1450
01:14:00.800 --> 01:14:02.320
So. why didn't you
tell your family?

1451
01:14:02.439 --> 01:14:05.280
I had trouble believing it.
Wanted to talk to Gabi first.

1452
01:14:05.560 --> 01:14:07.960
Oh. so she threw herself at you.
did she?

1453
01:14:08.040 --> 01:14:09.560
Beg you to keep quiet?

1454
01:14:09.840 --> 01:14:11.960
Or maybe it was the sex
you were always after.

1455
01:14:12.080 --> 01:14:13.280
No. I never...

1456
01:14:15.080 --> 01:14:17.560
-You never what?
-(sighs)

1457
01:14:21.080 --> 01:14:23.640
-It was the money.
-Money?

1458
01:14:24.040 --> 01:14:25.640
Mam gave Gabi
everything she wanted.

1459
01:14:26.240 --> 01:14:28.680
Poor girl. Vulnerable background.

1460
01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:31.080
(scoffs)
And then the cancer diagnosis.

1461
01:14:31.160 --> 01:14:33.720
And you needed money
for your business.

1462
01:14:33.800 --> 01:14:35.000
(Jonathon)
I'd asked Mam for a loan.

1463
01:14:35.600 --> 01:14:36.720
It hadn't gone well.

1464
01:14:37.920 --> 01:14:41.360
-But if Gabi tried...
-Yeah. so you used Gabi's secret

1465
01:14:41.920 --> 01:14:44.560
-to blackmail her into helping you.
-You really want to use

1466
01:14:44.640 --> 01:14:46.080
the word "blackmail"
where she's concerned?

1467
01:14:46.280 --> 01:14:49.439
Yeah. but no money was forthcoming.
But you still had the affair.

1468
01:14:50.000 --> 01:14:52.320
-She wanted it.
-No. please.

1469
01:14:53.520 --> 01:14:55.320
-Oh. hold up.
-(suspenseful music playing)

1470
01:14:55.560 --> 01:14:59.600
Now. he knew her secret.
but by sleeping with him...

1471
01:15:01.280 --> 01:15:04.640
the power switched
right back to Gabi. didn't it?

1472
01:15:05.400 --> 01:15:08.400
So. now you needed her
to keep quiet.

1473
01:15:10.120 --> 01:15:14.280
Now. she's not here to ask. pet.
So. why did you drive to Bewton?

1474
01:15:14.479 --> 01:15:16.680
Gabi rang. asked to be picked up.

1475
01:15:17.720 --> 01:15:19.439
-She didn't show.
-Yeah. what was she doing there?

1476
01:15:19.560 --> 01:15:21.520
(Jonathon) I don't know.
She was upset.

1477
01:15:21.600 --> 01:15:22.640
About what?

1478
01:15:22.720 --> 01:15:24.920
Something about things being ruined
with the family.

1479
01:15:25.479 --> 01:15:27.439
I thought Mam had found out
about the cancer.

1480
01:15:28.120 --> 01:15:30.240
So. I drove to pick her up.
She didn't show.

1481
01:15:30.320 --> 01:15:31.680
(Joe) You expect us
to believe that?

1482
01:15:32.000 --> 01:15:34.800
Look. I drove to pick her up.

1483
01:15:35.479 --> 01:15:39.520
She didn't show. So. I rang her.
She didn't answer.

1484
01:15:40.240 --> 01:15:41.320
So. I drove home.

1485
01:15:42.439 --> 01:15:43.520
Alone.

1486
01:15:44.640 --> 01:15:47.160
-(music concludes)
-Well. he's lied to us repeatedly.

1487
01:15:47.240 --> 01:15:49.960
he's got a clear motive.
and we can place him in the area.

1488
01:15:50.080 --> 01:15:51.360
Sounds pretty damning to me.

1489
01:15:51.520 --> 01:15:53.280
-(Vera) Aye. it does.
-(indistinct chatter)

1490
01:15:53.400 --> 01:15:55.960
But he said he didn't know
why she was out there

1491
01:15:56.040 --> 01:15:57.560
in the middle of nowhere.

1492
01:15:57.840 --> 01:16:01.080
Said she was upset and thought
his mam had found out the truth.

1493
01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:06.200
Now. if he really thought that.
and I'm inclined to believe him...

1494
01:16:07.280 --> 01:16:08.760
why would he kill Gabi?

1495
01:16:08.880 --> 01:16:10.920
-Everyone else is in the clear.
-(suspenseful music playing)

1496
01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:14.479
Helen. Fiona. Tom. Lee.
Everyone except Jonathon.

1497
01:16:15.760 --> 01:16:18.479
-But that phrase.
-What phrase?

1498
01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:22.800
Gabi accused Lee of
"Ruining it with the family."

1499
01:16:23.040 --> 01:16:25.600
And we all assumed
she meant that he'd exposed

1500
01:16:25.680 --> 01:16:29.880
her con to the Rushdens.
But there's another family in this.

1501
01:16:32.600 --> 01:16:34.520
We've been looking
at the wrong family.

1502
01:16:34.600 --> 01:16:35.640
(music concludes)

1503
01:16:35.720 --> 01:16:37.600
-(door knocking)
-(seagulls squawking)

1504
01:16:39.720 --> 01:16:42.479
(Vera) Hello. love. Quick question.

1505
01:16:43.160 --> 01:16:44.880
-Are yous releasing Lee?
-No.

1506
01:16:45.840 --> 01:16:47.160
-So what. then?
-(door closing)

1507
01:16:47.280 --> 01:16:49.439
Well. I just wanted to ask you

1508
01:16:50.800 --> 01:16:53.439
if you'd contacted Gabi's parents.

1509
01:16:54.800 --> 01:16:56.280
Er. her parents?

1510
01:16:56.400 --> 01:16:57.400
(Vera) Hmm.

1511
01:16:58.120 --> 01:17:00.479
-I...
-(Vera) Now. I can understand

1512
01:17:00.560 --> 01:17:02.439
why you'd want
Gabi off the scene. pet.

1513
01:17:03.040 --> 01:17:06.600
But personally. I think you can
do better than Lee Critchley.

1514
01:17:07.280 --> 01:17:09.439
But the heart wants
what the heart wants.

1515
01:17:09.520 --> 01:17:11.520
and you want him. right?

1516
01:17:12.520 --> 01:17:13.520
Yeah.

1517
01:17:14.000 --> 01:17:16.600
Now. we know
you accessed his phone.

1518
01:17:16.840 --> 01:17:19.520
read his messages.
Now. was there a number on there

1519
01:17:19.640 --> 01:17:20.840
for Gabi's parents?

1520
01:17:21.680 --> 01:17:25.840
Eh. when Gabi turned up.
it was obvious she was laying low.

1521
01:17:26.520 --> 01:17:28.439
Lee said her family
might be looking for her.

1522
01:17:29.360 --> 01:17:33.200
So. calling the parents would be
a good way to get rid. right?

1523
01:17:34.720 --> 01:17:36.240
I thought it was worth a try.

1524
01:17:37.080 --> 01:17:41.040
I. erm. took the number Lee had
and called it from my phone.

1525
01:17:41.160 --> 01:17:42.680
And what did you tell them?

1526
01:17:43.760 --> 01:17:46.080
I just gave him a number
to call Gabi on.

1527
01:17:46.280 --> 01:17:48.000
I told him she was in Newcastle

1528
01:17:48.680 --> 01:17:50.840
and that she was saying
she was sick.

1529
01:17:51.040 --> 01:17:52.600
(hesitates)
It was a short phone call.

1530
01:17:52.680 --> 01:17:54.400
-He hung up.
-He?

1531
01:17:54.479 --> 01:17:56.160
So. it was the father. Matthew?

1532
01:17:56.240 --> 01:17:58.040
Well. how come we haven't been able
to trace any calls

1533
01:17:58.120 --> 01:17:59.320
from the McSwains?

1534
01:18:03.080 --> 01:18:04.479
Thanks. pet.

1535
01:18:08.200 --> 01:18:11.120
(suspenseful music playing)

1536
01:18:12.560 --> 01:18:14.160
-Steph?
-(Steph) Ma'am?

1537
01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:20.040
This call came in a week ago.
Did you trace it?

1538
01:18:21.720 --> 01:18:23.120
Er. yeah. yeah. I did trace it.

1539
01:18:23.200 --> 01:18:25.640
Erm. it came
from some kind of boatyard.

1540
01:18:25.720 --> 01:18:26.760
Likely a wrong number.

1541
01:18:27.320 --> 01:18:29.600
Because this call
is five minutes long.

1542
01:18:29.680 --> 01:18:31.479
so it's no wrong number. love.

1543
01:18:32.000 --> 01:18:35.280
And McSwain's missus says
his boat was in for an overhaul.

1544
01:18:35.640 --> 01:18:37.720
Find out if they do repairs.
and if his boat was in.

1545
01:18:37.800 --> 01:18:40.080
-And if it was. when?
-(Steph) Ma'am.

1546
01:18:40.200 --> 01:18:41.960
Right. Let's get up there.

1547
01:18:45.800 --> 01:18:48.280
Okay. thanks. Steph. Good work.

1548
01:18:50.040 --> 01:18:51.840
What about McSwain's boat?

1549
01:18:52.360 --> 01:18:53.880
Well. it weren't in this place
last Wednesday.

1550
01:18:54.000 --> 01:18:55.120
It's only just come out.

1551
01:18:55.720 --> 01:18:58.320
So. he wasn't out on the sea
the day Gabi died.

1552
01:18:58.479 --> 01:19:00.200
Steph spoke to the boat builder.

1553
01:19:00.600 --> 01:19:02.040
Matthew asked to use
the office phone.

1554
01:19:02.120 --> 01:19:03.479
He said his mobile was dead.

1555
01:19:18.080 --> 01:19:20.200
(engine rumbles)

1556
01:19:21.840 --> 01:19:23.520
Right. You stay here.

1557
01:19:36.120 --> 01:19:39.120
(seagulls squawking)

1558
01:19:53.200 --> 01:19:54.360
Hey.

1559
01:19:55.560 --> 01:19:58.160
Oh. me dad always wanted
a boat like this.

1560
01:19:58.479 --> 01:19:59.920
Ah.

1561
01:20:00.960 --> 01:20:02.920
(Matthew) Yeah.
Not many of them left.

1562
01:20:03.040 --> 01:20:04.120
(Vera) Yeah.

1563
01:20:07.760 --> 01:20:08.800
Why are you here?

1564
01:20:09.680 --> 01:20:14.840
Ah. because I need to ask you
about a lass called Sian Jordan.

1565
01:20:16.080 --> 01:20:17.320
She rang you. didn't she?

1566
01:20:18.320 --> 01:20:19.680
Told you where Gabi was.

1567
01:20:24.280 --> 01:20:26.040
Picked up. She...

1568
01:20:27.160 --> 01:20:28.479
said it was about my daughter.

1569
01:20:29.360 --> 01:20:32.520
Hmm. And she gave you
a number to call Gabi.

1570
01:20:32.760 --> 01:20:34.840
And I did. Eventually.

1571
01:20:35.040 --> 01:20:38.640
And you rang from the boatyard
where this was being. er. repaired?

1572
01:20:39.920 --> 01:20:42.720
I was worried she might not pick up
if I used my own phone.

1573
01:20:42.800 --> 01:20:44.120
-Hmm.
-(dramatic music playing)

1574
01:20:44.240 --> 01:20:46.320
(Vera)
And you arranged to meet her?

1575
01:20:47.040 --> 01:20:48.040
(sighs)

1576
01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:50.400
-Yeah.
-Where?

1577
01:20:52.960 --> 01:20:57.880
There's a... a path we used to hike
when the kids were younger.

1578
01:20:58.800 --> 01:21:01.920
You know. quiet spot.
Well away from Debs.

1579
01:21:03.760 --> 01:21:06.000
-Deborah didn't know?
-Oh.

1580
01:21:06.120 --> 01:21:07.439
After everything
Gabi put her through.

1581
01:21:08.520 --> 01:21:12.160
I just... I just wanted
some honest answers.

1582
01:21:12.720 --> 01:21:13.840
And especially when...

1583
01:21:16.040 --> 01:21:17.520
the girl who rang...

1584
01:21:18.840 --> 01:21:21.160
said that Gabi had been saying
she was sick.

1585
01:21:21.320 --> 01:21:23.640
-Ah. did you know that wasn't true?
-(Matthew) No.

1586
01:21:24.280 --> 01:21:25.720
That's why I wanted to see her.

1587
01:21:27.000 --> 01:21:28.240
What's worse. eh?

1588
01:21:29.640 --> 01:21:31.320
A second daughter with cancer or...

1589
01:21:32.439 --> 01:21:35.520
or a daughter who'd fake
having what killed her sister.

1590
01:21:37.720 --> 01:21:39.360
She tried spinning her story
at first.

1591
01:21:39.520 --> 01:21:41.560
how she was getting back
on her feet...

1592
01:21:42.600 --> 01:21:45.120
was sorry for what
she put us through.

1593
01:21:46.160 --> 01:21:48.840
Until I questioned her
about this illness of hers.

1594
01:21:48.920 --> 01:21:50.520
And did she admit
what she'd been doing?

1595
01:21:51.040 --> 01:21:53.960
No. But she couldn't pretend.

1596
01:21:54.280 --> 01:21:55.520
Not to me.

1597
01:21:56.760 --> 01:21:57.880
She got angry.

1598
01:21:58.040 --> 01:21:59.720
(tense music playing)

1599
01:22:00.280 --> 01:22:04.360
Started saying that she was getting
the care and love

1600
01:22:04.439 --> 01:22:05.880
that she'd never got off me
and Debs.

1601
01:22:06.120 --> 01:22:08.880
-Ah. which made you angry?
-Of course. it did.

1602
01:22:10.120 --> 01:22:11.800
You know. because we had loved her.

1603
01:22:13.120 --> 01:22:14.439
And there she was.

1604
01:22:14.520 --> 01:22:17.640
play-acting at the horror
that Emma had gone through.

1605
01:22:18.800 --> 01:22:19.800
Polluting it.

1606
01:22:20.680 --> 01:22:21.680
It was sick.

1607
01:22:25.680 --> 01:22:26.800
I...

1608
01:22:28.400 --> 01:22:30.479
-I slapped her.
-(grunts softly)

1609
01:22:33.439 --> 01:22:34.560
And then she...

1610
01:22:35.320 --> 01:22:36.439
went for me.

1611
01:22:37.840 --> 01:22:41.800
-Screaming and shouting.
-You're a total bastard!

1612
01:22:41.880 --> 01:22:44.320
-(cries) She got everything!
-How dare you!

1613
01:22:44.479 --> 01:22:46.000
-(Gabi) Always!
-We did our best!

1614
01:22:46.160 --> 01:22:47.560
I got the leftovers!

1615
01:22:48.240 --> 01:22:50.439
(cries) I just...

1616
01:22:52.840 --> 01:22:54.040
I just grabbed her.

1617
01:22:55.040 --> 01:22:56.560
I was... I was furious.

1618
01:22:58.640 --> 01:23:00.680
(cries) I was shaking.
I was shouting at her. and then...

1619
01:23:00.840 --> 01:23:03.479
-Stupid. stupid little girl!
-(grunts)

1620
01:23:03.600 --> 01:23:05.320
(Matthew) And I pushed her.
and she fell over. and...

1621
01:23:05.479 --> 01:23:06.880
(cries)

1622
01:23:08.479 --> 01:23:09.600
I didn't...

1623
01:23:11.000 --> 01:23:12.439
I didn't even help her up.

1624
01:23:13.600 --> 01:23:15.040
(sniffles)

1625
01:23:15.680 --> 01:23:16.680
But she got up.

1626
01:23:18.320 --> 01:23:19.520
Yeah. of course. she did.

1627
01:23:21.040 --> 01:23:22.320
Her fight had gone. but. erm...

1628
01:23:24.160 --> 01:23:25.800
she was still screaming at me.
telling me that...

1629
01:23:26.880 --> 01:23:28.040
that she wanted me to go.

1630
01:23:28.320 --> 01:23:30.360
Get away!

1631
01:23:31.520 --> 01:23:33.080
Get away from me!

1632
01:23:34.400 --> 01:23:36.360
I never want to see you again!

1633
01:23:39.280 --> 01:23:40.280
(cries) So. I did.

1634
01:23:42.000 --> 01:23:43.040
I went.

1635
01:23:44.960 --> 01:23:46.080
I said...

1636
01:23:46.560 --> 01:23:47.600
Fine.

1637
01:23:48.680 --> 01:23:49.720
But that's it.

1638
01:23:50.960 --> 01:23:52.560
Hear me. Gabi? That is it.

1639
01:23:53.680 --> 01:23:55.840
We have no daughter.
You're dead to us.

1640
01:24:02.200 --> 01:24:03.360
(cries)

1641
01:24:08.680 --> 01:24:11.400
You should have told us
all of this before. love.

1642
01:24:11.640 --> 01:24:14.040
Oh. Debs couldn't know
that I'd seen Gabi.

1643
01:24:15.320 --> 01:24:17.800
Not that I'd had that chance.
and then that's how it ended.

1644
01:24:18.400 --> 01:24:20.560
And what difference would it make
anyway. eh?

1645
01:24:22.000 --> 01:24:23.120
(cries) When I...

1646
01:24:24.200 --> 01:24:26.200
When I left her
just for someone to... (sniffles)

1647
01:24:28.120 --> 01:24:30.800
(Vera)
Except there was no one else. love.

1648
01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:34.439
-Eh?
-It was you.

1649
01:24:35.160 --> 01:24:37.360
You shouldn't have left her
in that state.

1650
01:24:41.160 --> 01:24:42.240
(screams)

1651
01:24:44.320 --> 01:24:45.479
What was me?

1652
01:24:47.720 --> 01:24:49.080
When you pushed her...

1653
01:24:50.600 --> 01:24:53.280
the fall caused a clot here.

1654
01:24:54.960 --> 01:24:57.960
And that stopped blood
getting to her brain.

1655
01:25:01.840 --> 01:25:03.520
(sniffles)

1656
01:25:04.439 --> 01:25:05.520
(body thuds)

1657
01:25:07.680 --> 01:25:08.680
No.

1658
01:25:10.600 --> 01:25:12.120
I'm sorry. love.

1659
01:25:12.640 --> 01:25:13.640
No. (cries)

1660
01:25:24.200 --> 01:25:28.960
(screams. cries)

1661
01:25:49.040 --> 01:25:51.840
Well. you look better
than when I last saw you.

1662
01:25:51.960 --> 01:25:55.120
(chuckles) Ah. you know.
just taking it one day at a time.

1663
01:25:55.200 --> 01:25:56.600
-Ah.
-You need something?

1664
01:25:56.880 --> 01:25:58.840
Aye. me motor needs a service.

1665
01:25:58.960 --> 01:26:01.040
-And the MOT is due.
-(chuckles)

1666
01:26:02.080 --> 01:26:03.840
Well. I want it in safe hands.
love.

1667
01:26:03.920 --> 01:26:05.560
-Can you manage it?
-Of course.

1668
01:26:05.680 --> 01:26:07.560
-You can leave her here now.
-Hmm.

1669
01:26:08.920 --> 01:26:10.920
And a day at a time's good. love.

1670
01:26:11.760 --> 01:26:15.240
But I think your missus
might need you now more than ever.

1671
01:26:16.520 --> 01:26:18.640
I think you might be able
to salvage something

1672
01:26:18.720 --> 01:26:20.320
from all this mess.

1673
01:26:21.479 --> 01:26:22.720
You think about it.

1674
01:26:23.479 --> 01:26:25.120
(footsteps receding)

1675
01:26:27.400 --> 01:26:30.200
(Joe) You're unbelievable.
Shorten your car before your tooth.

1676
01:26:30.280 --> 01:26:31.960
Oh. priorities. Joe.

1677
01:26:33.120 --> 01:26:34.200
Anyway.

1678
01:26:35.240 --> 01:26:36.960
Guess where
you're dropping me next?

1679
01:26:37.080 --> 01:26:38.720
(perky music playing)

1680
01:26:40.160 --> 01:26:41.280
All right. the meter's running.

1681
01:26:43.880 --> 01:26:44.960
Everything go okay?

1682
01:26:46.680 --> 01:26:47.680
(Vera groans)

1683
01:26:47.840 --> 01:26:49.640
Thanks for waiting. Joe.
Much appreciated.

1684
01:26:53.160 --> 01:26:55.400
-Can't have been that bad.
-(Vera groaning) Injection...

1685
01:26:55.840 --> 01:26:57.320
(Joe) Oh. you're still numb.

1686
01:26:57.400 --> 01:26:59.160
Well. a quiet day
for the rest of us. then.

1687
01:27:06.920 --> 01:27:09.920
(sombre music playing)

1688
01:27:23.920 --> 01:27:25.320
(Deborah breathes deeply)

1689
01:27:27.400 --> 01:27:28.560
I'm so sorry.

1690
01:27:30.200 --> 01:27:31.400
What she put you through.

1691
01:27:32.680 --> 01:27:33.680
No.

1692
01:27:34.400 --> 01:27:37.200
I can't say you've been any worse
a mother than me.

1693
01:27:56.400 --> 01:27:57.600
Thank you.

1694
01:28:05.240 --> 01:28:06.720
(kisses)

1695
01:28:12.520 --> 01:28:14.040
(crosswalk beeping)

1696
01:28:25.320 --> 01:28:26.400
(bicycle bell dinging)

1697
01:28:46.520 --> 01:28:48.160
(theme music playing)

1698
01:29:14.280 --> 01:29:16.240
{\an8}(theme music concludes)
